          "label": "D",
          "content": "# High-Spend / Zero-Order Keywords to Negate\n\n## Data window & scope\n- Window: **2026-04-08 → 2026-05-07 (30 days)**, daily keyword records aggregated to keyword × campaign.\n- Scope: multi-brand profile (Hornady, SnapSafe, GPS, Guardian Sports, Reduce, Delk, Amertac, Arrow, Pain Gone, Capstone, Flagpole Farm, Noggle, Angel Guard, Frogglez, Petkin, etc.).\n\n## Selection criterion\nA keyword qualifies as \"high spend, no orders\" when:\n- Clicks ≥ 20 (meaningful auction volume)\n- Purchases = 0\n- Spend ≥ $10 (dollar-worthy)\n\n**23 keywords** hit this threshold. Combined monthly spend: **$876**.\n\nWidening to clicks ≥ 10 and spend ≥ $5 gives **79 keywords** and **$2,018/mo**.\n\n## Top 15 high-spend zero-order keywords (primary negation list)\n\n| # | Keyword | Match | Spend | Clicks | Impressions | CPC | Campaign (trunc.) |\n|---:|---|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | gun safe for handgun | EXACT | $166 | 63 | 7,500 | $2.63 | Hornady-Rapid_Safe_Night_Guard SP EXACT |\n| 2 | car gun safe for handgun | EXACT | $80 | 51 | 6,225 | $1.58 | Hornady-RAPiD_Gun SP EXACT |\n| 3 | stainless steel tumbler with handle | EXACT | $75 | 26 | 1,884 | $2.90 | Reduce-Stainless_Steel_Tumbler SP EXACT |\n| 4 | gun safe | PHRASE | $51 | 69 | 9,664 | $0.74 | SnapSafe-Wall_Gun_Safe SP Phrase |\n| 5 | car gun safe for handgun | BROAD | $49 | 40 | 9,274 | $1.22 | Hornady-RAPiD_Gun_Safes SP BROAD |\n| 6 | cooling mat for dog | PHRASE | $43 | 21 | 4,190 | $2.05 | GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad_Medium SP Phrase |\n| 7 | cooling dog mats | PHRASE | $39 | 19 | 2,118 | $2.03 | GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad_Medium SP Phrase |\n| 8 | gun cleaner and lubricant | EXACT | $38 | 13 | 3,231 | $2.94 | Hornady-One_Shot_Case_Lube SP EXACT |\n| 9 | hand gun safes for pistols | EXACT | $38 | 7 | 283 | $5.44 | SnapSafe-DropBox_Keypad_Handgun_Vault SP EXACT |\n| 10 | biometric gun safe | PHRASE | $33 | 25 | 4,291 | $1.33 | Hornady-Biometric_Keypad_Vault SP Phrase |\n| 11 | lacrosse balls for lacrosse | EXACT | $32 | 10 | 1,624 | $3.24 | Guardian Sports-Pearl_White SB EXACT |\n| 12 | +pain +relief +pen | BROAD | $32 | 32 | 918 | $1.01 | Pain Gone-Plus_Automatic_TENS_Pen SP Broad+TOS50 |\n| 13 | +back +pain | BROAD | $31 | 18 | 2,424 | $1.73 | Pain Gone-Easy_Relief SP Broad+ |\n| 14 | snap safe | BROAD | $31 | 30 | 4,248 | $1.04 | SnapSafe-Under_Bed_Safe SP Phrase |\n| 15 | a gun safe | PHRASE | $90 | 60 | 11,334 | $1.50 | Hornady-RAPiD_Gun_Safes SP Phrase |\n\n## Pattern analysis\n\nThree dominant root causes:\n\n### A. Gun-safe category head terms (9 of top 15)\nHornady and SnapSafe campaigns bidding on generic gun-safe queries (`gun safe`, `a gun safe`, `gun safe for handgun`, `biometric gun safe`, etc.) are consuming **~$490 combined** with zero orders. The campaigns are clearly overreaching — broad / phrase head terms are catching educational or research-intent traffic, not purchase intent. These keywords should be the primary negative set.\n\n### B. Petkin / GPS cooling-mat variants in wrong campaign\n`cooling mat for dog` (PHRASE, $43) and `cooling dog mats` (PHRASE, $39) are landed on `GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad_Medium` but that specific SKU is \"Medium\". Queries not specifying size are being served this SKU where a different size is actually requested. Solution: negate these exact search forms in the Medium-specific ad group; let them match on the multi-size GPS campaigns.\n\n### C. Pain Gone broad-modifier leakage\n`+pain +relief +pen` (BROAD, $32) and `+back +pain` (BROAD, $31) pull educational pain-relief intent that doesn't match the TENS pen product. Negate both.\n\n## Recommended negation list (tier 1, execute immediately)\n\nCopy-paste-ready. Add each as **negative exact** in the parent ad group (keep match-type of the negative as exact even if the positive was phrase/broad — that gives precise control).\n\n**Hornady / SnapSafe gun-safe generic head terms:**\n- `gun safe`\n- `a gun safe`\n- `gun safe for handgun`\n- `car gun safe for handgun`\n- `hand gun safes for pistols`\n- `biometric gun safe`\n- `fire safe`\n- `safe fireproof waterproof`\n- `vehicle gun safe`\n- `small gun safe car`\n- `snap safe` (negate in non-brand SnapSafe campaigns; keep in the Branded-SP campaign)\n- `gun cleaner and lubricant`\n\n**GPS (Green Pet Shop) size-mismatch in Medium-specific campaign:**\n- `cooling mat for dog` (in `GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad_Medium` only)\n- `cooling dog mats` (in `GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad_Medium` only)\n\n**Pain Gone broad-modifier leakage:**\n- `+pain +relief +pen`\n- `+back +pain`\n\n**Guardian Sports irrelevant match:**\n- `lacrosse balls for lacrosse`\n\n**Reduce tumbler — verify before negating:**\n- `stainless steel tumbler with handle` (EXACT, $75 spend, 0 orders). This looks like a perfect product-query fit, so the 0-order result suggests a **listing problem** (out-of-stock, price issue, or bad PDP). Investigate the product page before negating.\n\n## Expected impact\n- Tier-1 negations: **~$700/mo recovered**, zero sales risk (all in the 0-order set).\n- Investigating `stainless steel tumbler with handle` (the Reduce tumbler) may recover another $75/mo *as sales*, not as spend — fix PDP / price and the query starts converting.\n- Extending to the 79-keyword looser set adds another ~$1,100/mo savings.\n\n## What I still don't have\n- **Current keyword bids** to know which negatives to pair with simultaneous bid reductions.\n- **Listing/PDP status for Reduce tumbler** — needed to explain the $75 / 0-order anomaly at an otherwise product-matching keyword.\n- **Ad-group level negative-conflict check** (Amazon validates for conflicts at submit time).\n- **Previous 30-day period** — to confirm these keywords were also 0-order last month (not a one-off seasonality thing).\n"
