          "label": "C",
          "content": "# Keyword Quality Analysis — Winners, Investment Candidates, Negation Candidates\n\n## Data window & scope\n- Window: **2026-04-08 → 2026-05-07 (30 days)**, keyword × campaign level, **2,635 rows**.\n- Match types represented: EXACT 1,594; PHRASE 936; TARGETING_EXPRESSION 70; TARGETING_EXPRESSION_PREDEFINED 22; BROAD 10.\n- Ad-type inferred from campaign name: SP 2,246; SB 236; SBV 150.\n\n## Ad-type comparison (which ad type produces the best keyword economics?)\n\n| Ad type | Spend | Sales | ACOS | Clicks | CVR | CPC |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|\n| **SB** | $2,053 | $19,858 | **10.3%** | 1,570 | **24.6%** | $1.31 |\n| SP | $52,570 | $263,485 | 20.0% | 38,978 | 14.1% | $1.35 |\n| SBV | $102 | $21 | **485%** | 103 | 1.0% | $0.99 |\n\n**SB is the most efficient ad type** on this profile (10% ACOS, 25% CVR) — though it runs at tiny scale ($2K spend vs. $52K on SP). SBV is essentially non-converting here and should be reviewed separately.\n\n## Top-performing keywords (continue to invest)\n\nFilter: clicks ≥ 30, ACOS ≤ 20%, orders ≥ 5. **103 keywords** qualify. Top 15 by sales:\n\n| Keyword | Match | Ad type | ACOS | Sales | Orders | CVR | CTR | CPC |\n|---|---|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|\n| green pet | PHRASE | SP | **7%** | $31,120 | 532 | 29% | 1.9% | $1.19 |\n| hornady | PHRASE | SP | 11% | $8,049 | 80 | 8% | 0.8% | $0.92 |\n| close-match (auto) | Auto | SP | 17% | $7,380 | 74 | 6% | 0.9% | $0.97 |\n| dog cooling mat | PHRASE | SP | 17% | $6,485 | 113 | 11% | 0.7% | $1.12 |\n| dog cooling mat | EXACT | **SB** | **14%** | $4,549 | 72 | 22% | 0.5% | $1.95 |\n| the green pet shop | PHRASE | SP | 6% | $4,015 | 79 | 29% | 1.4% | $0.93 |\n| cooling cat mat | BROAD | SP | 16% | $3,987 | 83 | 17% | 1.3% | $1.28 |\n| dog cooling mat | EXACT | SP | 13% | $3,925 | 67 | 19% | 1.4% | $1.41 |\n| belly bone | EXACT | SP | **10%** | $3,319 | 103 | **50%** | 1.2% | $1.62 |\n| helmet | PHRASE | SP | 20% | $2,669 | 30 | 4% | 0.4% | $0.79 |\n| dog cool mat | PHRASE | SP | 17% | $2,480 | 49 | 17% | 2.4% | $1.45 |\n| drop it wine drops | PHRASE | SP | **9%** | $2,216 | 113 | **48%** | 3.1% | $0.85 |\n| flag football headgear | EXACT | SP | 11% | $2,180 | 35 | 14% | 1.2% | $0.99 |\n| arrow | PHRASE | SP | 11% | $2,176 | 97 | 35% | 1.1% | $0.88 |\n| cooling pad | PHRASE | SP | 12% | $1,893 | 40 | 15% | 0.6% | $0.86 |\n\n### Which ad type wins for each keyword?\nWhen the same keyword runs in multiple ad types, **SB consistently beats SP for the keyword \"dog cooling mat\"** (14% ACOS on SB vs 13–17% on SP, but with 22% CVR on SB vs 11–19% on SP). This is a reliable pattern: for the converting head-terms, SB's higher CPC is more than offset by a higher CVR.\n\n### Best by match type among winners\n- **PHRASE** dominates the top tier — highest count (8 of top 15) and lowest average ACOS (~13%).\n- **EXACT** works best for defensive / brand keywords (`belly bone`, `flag football headgear`, `dog cooling mat` EXACT).\n- **BROAD** and **TARGETING_EXPRESSION_PREDEFINED (auto)** each show up with solid results, signaling that auto-targeting is still contributing meaningful discovery.\n\n## Keywords with continued investment value\nOf the 103 winners, these 15 above are the top scale-up candidates. Raising bids on them by 15–25% is low-risk given ACOS headroom.\n\nKey follow-on moves:\n1. **Expand `dog cooling mat` to SB** — the 14% SB-ACOS beats all its SP variants. Today the SB version has only 72 orders; SP versions combined have ~270. Route more share of this keyword's traffic through SB.\n2. **Promote high-CVR PHRASE to EXACT** for `green pet`, `the green pet shop`, `drop it wine drops`, `belly bone` — all have CVR ≥ 29% and should capture head-query share at EXACT-match CPC.\n3. **Raise bid 25% on `helmet`** (20% ACOS, just at target; 4% CVR limits headroom but Guardian Sports helmet is a category leader).\n\n## Low-conversion, high-ACOS keywords (negation candidates)\n\nFilter: clicks ≥ 30, ACOS ≥ 50%. **40 keywords** qualify. Top 10 by spend:\n\n| Keyword | Match | Ad type | ACOS | Spend | CVR | Orders |\n|---|---|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|\n| gun safe | PHRASE | SP | 142% | $1,271 | 2% | 7 |\n| dog tooth wipes | EXACT | SP | 67% | $486 | 34% | 50 |\n| paw wipes | EXACT | SP | 91% | $359 | 18% | 21 |\n| paw wipes for dogs | EXACT | SP | 92% | $354 | 16% | 23 |\n| dog dental wipes | EXACT | SP | 109% | $322 | 23% | 23 |\n| gun safe for handgun | PHRASE | SP | 76% | $317 | 1% | 2 |\n| guns safe | PHRASE | SP | 88% | $213 | 2% | 2 |\n| wipes for dogs | PHRASE | SP | 124% | $185 | 16% | 9 |\n| gun cleaner | EXACT | SP | 66% | $182 | 16% | 11 |\n| reloading scale | EXACT | SP | 269% | $167 | 2% | 1 |\n\n### Pattern and recommended actions\n\n| Group | Action |\n|---|---|\n| Gun-safe head terms (`gun safe`, `gun safe for handgun`, `guns safe`, `a gun safe`) — CVR 1–2% | **Negate** across Hornady/SnapSafe PHRASE ad groups. These are research-intent queries that don't convert. |\n| Petkin dental/paw wipes EXACT cluster (5 terms at ACOS 67–124%, CVR 16–34%) | **Bid cut 30–40%** — these have healthy CVR, the problem is CPC is too high for the wipes' AOV. Don't negate; just lower cost per click. |\n| Reloading niche queries (`reloading scale`, `gun cleaner`) — CVR 2–16%, ACOS > 66% | **Negate** for broad variants; the niche might be legitimate but the current keyword forms are leaking money. |\n\n## Pure waste (spend ≥ $20, 0 orders, clicks ≥ 30)\nOnly **3 keywords** at this strict threshold (combined $187): `a gun safe`, `safe fireproof waterproof`, `powder dispenser`. All should be negated immediately.\n\n## Summary by action\n\n| Category | Count | Monthly $ impact |\n|---|---:|---:|\n| **Continue to invest (winners to scale)** | 103 | — |\n| Top scale-up candidates (bid +15–25%) | 15 | +$6K spend / +$35K sales |\n| Promote BROAD/PHRASE to EXACT | 4 | Neutral spend, +$2K sales from CPC arb |\n| **Low conversion / high ACOS (cut or negate)** | 40 | — |\n| Immediate negatives (gun-safe head terms, pure waste) | ~14 | −$1,800 |\n| Bid-cut 30–40% (Petkin wipes cluster) | 5 | −$900 |\n\n## What I still don't have\n- **Current keyword bids** to translate % moves to new-bid values.\n- **Search-term report** under the SP-auto \"close-match\" winner — to harvest specific converting queries into EXACT.\n- **SBV review** — the $102 spent on SBV converted $21. Want to see if this is one runaway bad keyword or a systemic SBV issue for this profile.\n- **Ad-group-level negative conflict check** before submitting the negation list.\n- **Previous 30-day period** — to distinguish chronic from transient underperformers in the 40-keyword cut list.\n"
