          "content": "Based on the data provided for the last 30 days (spanning **2026-04-09 to 2026-05-08**), here is the breakdown of your ad-attributed sales. \n\nFirst, it is important to clarify a quick terminology distinction regarding Amazon Ads reports to ensure we are answering your exact question:\n1. **Advertised-Product Sales (`metric.salesPromoted`)**: These are the ad-attributed sales of the *specific products* you featured in your ads.\n2. **Purchased-Product Sales (`metric.sales`)**: This represents the *total ad-attributed brand sales*. It includes the advertised products **plus** any other products from your brand that shoppers bought after clicking your ad (known as the \"Brand Halo\" effect).\n3. **Total Overall Brand Sales**: Standard advertising reports do not include *organic* sales. To find the true percentage of your entire business driven by ads (Ads vs. Organic), we would need to compare this ad data against your Seller/Vendor Central business reports.\n\nAssuming you are looking for the breakdown between your **direct advertised product sales** versus your **total ad-driven brand sales** (the comparison between the advertised-product and purchased-product reports), here is the analysis based on the 100 campaigns provided in the summary:\n\n### 📊 Sales Breakdown (Last 30 Days)\n\n*   **Total Ad-Attributed Brand Sales** (Purchased-Product equivalent): **~$264,897**\n*   **Ad-Attributed Promoted Sales** (Advertised-Product equivalent): **~$109,093**\n\n### 💡 Key Insights & Share of Sales\n\n*   **Direct Ad Sales Share (41.2%)**: Approximately **41%** of your ad-driven revenue comes directly from shoppers buying the exact products you are advertising.\n*   **Brand Halo Share (58.8%)**: A massive **59%** of your ad-driven revenue comes from the **Brand Halo effect**. This means the majority of shoppers are clicking on your ads, navigating your catalog/storefront, and ultimately purchasing *different* products from your brand.\n\n**Expert Takeaway:**\nYour ads are acting as a highly effective top-of-funnel discovery tool. Campaigns like *GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad-MULTI-NB-SP-Exact* generated over $37,000 in total brand sales, but only ~$6,898 of that came from the promoted ASIN itself. This indicates excellent cross-selling and brand appeal, meaning your advertising is successfully lifting your entire catalog, not just the ASINs you are paying to promote."
