          "label": "A",
          "content": "# Impression Change Driver Analysis\n\nQuestion: Why has overall account impression volume changed over the last 14 days? Test against bid changes, budget changes, search-volume changes (proxy: impressions per keyword), and campaign-status changes.\n\nBusiness data used: campaign-level advertising performance, keyword, search-term, and targeting performance, campaign configuration, budget, and status snapshots. Time basis: 2026-04-25/2026-05-08; 2026-04-25/2026-05-01; 2026-04-25/2026-05-06. Monetary values follow the numeric currency basis present in the business data; no additional FX conversion was applied.\n\n## Largest campaign-level impression changes, week 2 vs week 1\n\n| campaign | week1 imps | week2 imps | delta | week1 CPC | week2 CPC |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| FlagpoleFarm-Titan_Telescoping_Flagpole_Kit-MULTI-N… | 35,908 | 2,417 | -33,491 | $4.33 | $2.01 |\n| GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad_Medium-B0DNLNQ4T1-NB-SP-E… | 0 | 27,065 | 27,065 | n/a | $1.99 |\n| Frogglez-Swim_Goggles_Kids_Blue-B075JN6XZN-NB-SP-EX… | 1,766 | 26,818 | 25,052 | $1.69 | $1.61 |\n| Hornady-One_Shot-MULTI-NB-SP-Exact | 29,543 | 5,359 | -24,184 | $2.32 | n/a |\n| GuardianSports-GC_Helmet_Cover-MULTI-NB-SP-PHRASE | 12,187 | 34,381 | 22,194 | $0.85 | $0.69 |\n| Frogglez-Swim_Goggles_Kids-MULTI-NB-SP-EXACT | 1,412 | 20,896 | 19,484 | $1.59 | $1.55 |\n| Petkin-Paw_Wipes_Orange-MULTI-NB-SP-Exact | 4,172 | 21,148 | 16,976 | $2.65 | $2.22 |\n| GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase | 62,604 | 45,684 | -16,920 | $1.40 | $1.50 |\n| Petkin-Pet_Dental_Wipes-MULTI-NB-SP-Exact | 3,759 | 18,518 | 14,759 | $3.60 | $2.41 |\n| SnapSafe-Treklite_Gun_Safe_Lock_Box-MULTI-NB-SP-Auto | 17,943 | 3,884 | -14,059 | $0.88 | $0.89 |\n\n## Readout\n\nThe business data supports an impression-change analysis at campaign level. Where impressions rose while CPC was flat or lower, the likely driver is more available traffic/search volume or broader serving. Where impressions fell and CPC rose, bid competitiveness or auction pressure may be contributing. However, the business data does not include actual bid changes, budget changes, campaign status changes, or hourly/day-level delivery status, so those drivers cannot be directly verified.\n\nData still needed: bid history, campaign budgets by day, campaign status history, and keyword-level week 1 vs week 2 impressions. The current `business data slice` is useful for identifying high-impression keywords but not for period-over-period keyword movement.\n"
