          "content": "# Top Campaign Spend Increases and Drivers\n\nQuestion: The 5 campaigns with the largest spend increase in the last 30 days. For each, identify whether the increase was driven by bid changes, budget changes, or search-volume tailwinds.\n\nBusiness data used: campaign-level advertising performance, campaign configuration, budget, and status snapshots. Time basis: 2026-04-09/2026-05-08; 2026-03-10/2026-04-08; 2026-03-10/2026-04-07. Monetary values follow the numeric currency basis present in the business data; no additional FX conversion was applied.\n\n## Top spend increases\n\n| campaign | prior spend | recent spend | increase | prior imps | recent imps | prior CPC | recent CPC | driver |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad-MULTI-NB-SP-Exa… | $1,018.94 | $8,038.11 | $7,019.17 | 55,413 | 520,237 | $1.40 | $1.75 | search-volume/impression tailwind + higher CPC / bid pressure + more clicks |\n| GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad-MULTI-NB-SP-Phr… | $421.36 | $4,546.98 | $4,125.62 | 23,106 | 291,319 | $1.35 | $1.38 | search-volume/impression tailwind + more clicks |\n| GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad-MULTI-NB-SP-Exact | $500.27 | $2,686.46 | $2,186.19 | 39,559 | 289,578 | $1.38 | $1.65 | search-volume/impression tailwind + higher CPC / bid pressure + more clicks |\n| Hornady-Fireproof_Safe_for_Guns_and_Valua… | $1.90 | $1,678.66 | $1,676.76 | 25 | 111,613 | $1.90 | $1.83 | search-volume/impression tailwind + more clicks |\n| GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad-MULTI-Branded-S… | $647.67 | $2,280.33 | $1,632.66 | 27,961 | 97,257 | $1.09 | $1.18 | search-volume/impression tailwind + more clicks |\n\n## Readout\n\nThe strongest spend increases are mostly accompanied by much higher impressions and clicks, so search-volume or traffic availability is the clearest supported driver. Where CPC also increased, bid pressure or bid changes may have amplified the spend lift. Budget-change attribution cannot be directly verified because the business data does not include budget history.\n\nData still needed: daily campaign budgets, bid history, campaign status changes, and daily pacing to cleanly distinguish budget changes from bid and search-volume effects.\n"
