          "label": "D",
          "content": "> **Query assumptions:** Time range is inferred as the last 30 days (April 9 – May 8, 2026). Only campaigns with Spend > 0 are included to ensure ACOS is meaningful. The 5 campaigns with the highest ACOS are selected as the \"worst performers.\" ASIN-type analysis is based on productAd meta data linked to each campaign. Please let me know if you'd like to adjust any of these parameters.\n\n---\n\n## 🔑 Key Findings\n\n1. **All 5 campaigns are Sponsored Products (SP) with Manual targeting** — this is a universal pattern, not a coincidence.\n2. **4 out of 5 use SP Fixed Bids + Phrase match keywords** — a rigid bidding and targeting setup with no algorithmic cost control, making overspend structurally likely.\n3. **ACOS ranges from 164% to 244%** — all are severely above any reasonable target, with spend far exceeding sales across the board.\n4. **No shared ASIN category pattern** — the poor performance cuts across unrelated product types (pet wipes, taco plates, gun lock boxes), suggesting the issue is structural/strategic rather than category-specific.\n\n---\n\n## 📊 Campaign Summary\n\n\n| Campaign Name | ACOS (%) | Spend (USD) | Sales (USD) | Ad Type | Targeting Type | Bidding Strategy | Match Types | # Promoted ASINs | ASIN Categories | Avg ASIN Price (USD) |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"Petkin-Mega_Pet_Wipes-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase\">Petkin-Mega_Pet_Wipes-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase</Link> | 243.8 | 155.64 | 63.84 | Sponsored Products | Manual | SP Fixed bids | Keyword-Phrase | 4 | Grooming Wipes, Grooming & Health Supplies | $16.84 |\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"Arrow-Home_Products_Fiesta_Taco_Plate-MULTI-NB-SP-PHRASE\">Arrow-Home_Products_Fiesta_Taco_Plate-MULTI-NB-SP-PHRASE</Link> | 235.92 | 80.12 | 33.96 | Sponsored Products | Manual | SP Fixed bids | Keyword-Phrase | 4 | Taco Holders, Dinner Plates, V4 Customers Keep It - 50% | $17.54 |\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"SnapSafe-Treklite_Gun_Safe_Lock_Box-B06XQVYY24-NB-SP-Phrase\">SnapSafe-Treklite_Gun_Safe_Lock_Box-B06XQVYY24-NB-SP-Phrase</Link> | 183.21 | 309.92 | 169.16 | Sponsored Products | Manual | SP Fixed bids | Keyword-Phrase | 1 | Security Lock Boxes | $30.94 |\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"SnapSafe-Treklite_Gun_Safe_Lock_Box-B06XQVYY24-NB-CNQ-SP-CAT\">SnapSafe-Treklite_Gun_Safe_Lock_Box-B06XQVYY24-NB-CNQ-SP-CAT</Link> | 164.95 | 248.59 | 150.71 | Sponsored Products | Manual | SP Dynamic bids - down only | asinPriceGreaterThan | 1 | Security Lock Boxes | $30.94 |\n| <Link entity=\"campaign\" name=\"Petkin-MegaValuPak_Pet_Wipes-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase\">Petkin-MegaValuPak_Pet_Wipes-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase</Link> | 164.24 | 285.02 | 173.54 | Sponsored Products | Manual | SP Fixed bids | Keyword-Phrase | 4 | Pet Birthday, Cat Supplies Subscribe & Save, Grooming Wipes, Dog Supplies Subscribe & Save, Top Cat Supplies, Top Dog Supplies, Pets Supplies Subscribe & Save, Grooming & Health Supplies | $12.72 |\n\n---\n\n## 🔍 Common Pattern Analysis\n\n\nThe table below flags dimensions where **3 or more of the 5 campaigns share the same characteristic**:\n\n| Dimension | Value | # Campaigns | Common Pattern? |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Ad Type | Sponsored Products | 5 | Yes |\n| Targeting Type | Manual | 5 | Yes |\n| Bidding Strategy | SP Fixed bids | 4 | Yes |\n| Dominant Targeting Type (from Targets) | Keyword | 4 | Yes |\n| Match Type | Keyword-Phrase | 4 | Yes |\n| ASIN Category | Grooming Wipes | 2 | No |\n| ASIN Category | Grooming & Health Supplies | 2 | No |\n| ASIN Category | Security Lock Boxes | 2 | No |\n| Bidding Strategy | SP Dynamic bids - down only | 1 | No |\n| Dominant Targeting Type (from Targets) | Product Targeting | 1 | No |\n| Match Type | asinPriceGreaterThan | 1 | No |\n| ASIN Category | Taco Holders | 1 | No |\n| ASIN Category | Dinner Plates | 1 | No |\n| ASIN Category | V4 Customers Keep It - 50% | 1 | No |\n| ASIN Category | Pet Birthday | 1 | No |\n| ASIN Category | Cat Supplies Subscribe & Save | 1 | No |\n| ASIN Category | Dog Supplies Subscribe & Save | 1 | No |\n| ASIN Category | Top Cat Supplies | 1 | No |\n| ASIN Category | Top Dog Supplies | 1 | No |\n| ASIN Category | Pets Supplies Subscribe & Save | 1 | No |\n\n---\n\n## 📝 Dimensional Breakdown\n\n### 1. Ad Type — ⚠️ Universal Pattern (5/5)\nAll 5 campaigns are **Sponsored Products**. This is the most common ad type in the account, so it's expected to dominate — but it also means all structural issues below are SP-specific.\n\n### 2. Targeting Type — ⚠️ Universal Pattern (5/5)\nEvery campaign uses **Manual targeting**. There are no Auto campaigns in this group. Manual targeting requires well-researched, well-maintained keyword/target lists to perform efficiently — if the keyword selection is poor or bids are not actively managed, ACOS will spiral.\n\n### 3. Bidding Strategy — ⚠️ Strong Pattern (4/5)\n**SP Fixed Bids** is used by 4 of the 5 campaigns. Fixed bids do not adjust based on conversion likelihood — the system bids the same amount regardless of placement or context. This is the most aggressive bidding strategy in terms of spend risk: there is no downward adjustment when conversion probability is low. One campaign uses \"SP Dynamic bids - down only,\" which at least allows the system to reduce bids when a conversion is less likely.\n\n### 4. Match Type — ⚠️ Strong Pattern (4/5)\n**Keyword Phrase match** is the dominant (and in most cases, only) match type across 4 campaigns. Phrase match is broader than exact match, meaning these campaigns are likely capturing a wide range of search queries — many of which may be irrelevant or low-converting. Without active negative keyword management, phrase match + fixed bids is a high-spend, low-efficiency combination.\n\nOne campaign uses `asinPriceGreaterThan` product targeting (price-based ASIN targeting), which is a different strategy but still resulted in a 165% ACOS.\n\n### 5. ASIN Categories — ❌ No Shared Pattern\nThe promoted ASINs span completely different categories: **pet wipes, taco plates, and gun lock boxes**. There is no category-level commonality. This rules out a category-specific issue (e.g., low demand, high competition in one niche) as the root cause. The problem is structural, not product-specific.\n\n### 6. ASIN Price — Moderate Range ($12–$31 avg)\nAverage ASIN prices range from ~$13 to ~$31. These are relatively low-to-mid price point products. With CPCs around $0.44–$2.94, the conversion economics are tight — a single click that doesn't convert represents a meaningful percentage of the product's sale price, making high ACOS structurally easier to accumulate.\n\n---\n\n## 💡 What These Campaigns Have in Common — Summary\n\n| Dimension | Common Pattern | Detail |\n|-----------|---------------|--------|\n| Ad Type | ✅ All 5 | Sponsored Products only |\n| Targeting Type | ✅ All 5 | Manual targeting |\n| Bidding Strategy | ✅ 4 of 5 | SP Fixed Bids (no downward adjustment) |\n| Match Type | ✅ 4 of 5 | Keyword Phrase match |\n| ASIN Category | ❌ None | Diverse categories — not a category issue |\n| AI Management | ⚠️ Mixed | Campaigns belong to AI groups (aiGroupId present), but bidding strategy is Fixed Bids — worth verifying whether AI bid optimization is actively enabled for these campaigns |\n\n**The structural signature of these 5 campaigns:** Manual SP campaigns, running phrase-match keywords, with fixed bids and no algorithmic cost control — a setup that will consistently overspend unless keyword lists are tightly curated and bids are actively managed. The fact that this pattern appears across unrelated product categories confirms it is a campaign configuration issue, not a product or market issue."
