          "content": "> **Assumptions applied — please confirm or adjust:**\n> - Performance data covers the last 7 days: **2026-05-02 to 2026-05-08**\n> - Account-level target ACOS is derived as the **simple average of targetAcos across all 71 enabled AI groups**, resulting in **20.50%**\n> - Only **positive keywords** (exact/phrase/broad) within fully enabled campaign chains are included\n> - Proposed new bid formula: `New Bid = Current Bid × (Target ACOS / Actual ACOS)`; projected spend is scaled proportionally\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 Key Findings\n\n1. **Account target ACOS benchmark: 20.50%** — derived from 71 enabled AI groups\n2. **All 10 keywords require bid reductions**, ranging from **−13.3% to −67.7%**, reflecting meaningful overspend relative to target\n3. **Projected total spend reduction: ~$727 over 7 days** (from ~$2,674 to ~$1,931), a **−27.2% decrease** across these 10 keywords\n4. **\"dog tooth wipes\" (exact) is the most extreme outlier** at 63.95% ACOS — nearly 3× the target — warranting the steepest bid cut (−67.7%, from $1.55 → $0.50); verify whether this keyword has sufficient conversion volume to justify continued investment\n\n---\n\n\n## Bid Adjustment Recommendations\n\n**Account Target ACOS: 20.50%** | Period: May 2–8, 2026 (7 days)\n\n| Keyword | Match Type | Current Bid (USD) | Proposed Bid (USD) | Bid Δ (USD) | Bid Δ % | Spend 7d (USD) | Proj. Spend 7d (USD) | Proj. Spend Δ (USD) | Actual ACOS % | Target ACOS % |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| cooling mat dogs | exact | 1.77 | 1.36 | -0.41 | -23.16 | 981.89 | 754.45 | -227.44 | 26.75 | 20.5 |\n| cooling mat for dog | exact | 1.93 | 1.5 | -0.43 | -22.28 | 487.05 | 378.54 | -108.51 | 26.39 | 20.5 |\n| cooling pad for dog | exact | 1.57 | 1.29 | -0.28 | -17.83 | 244.51 | 200.9 | -43.61 | 24.88 | 20.5 |\n| cooling mat for dogs | phrase | 1.37 | 0.8 | -0.57 | -41.61 | 239.25 | 139.71 | -99.54 | 35.19 | 20.5 |\n| case trimmer | phrase | 1.43 | 1.24 | -0.19 | -13.29 | 174.14 | 151 | -23.14 | 23.71 | 20.5 |\n| wine glass cover | exact | 0.8 | 0.63 | -0.17 | -21.25 | 118.65 | 93.44 | -25.21 | 25.98 | 20.5 |\n| cooling mat dogs | exact | 1.16 | 0.6 | -0.56 | -48.28 | 113.66 | 58.79 | -54.87 | 39.89 | 20.5 |\n| case trimmer reloading | phrase | 2.4 | 1.48 | -0.92 | -38.33 | 112.66 | 69.47 | -43.19 | 33.25 | 20.5 |\n| drop it | phrase | 0.84 | 0.56 | -0.28 | -33.33 | 102.67 | 68.45 | -34.22 | 30.66 | 20.5 |\n| dog tooth wipes | exact | 1.55 | 0.5 | -1.05 | -67.74 | 99.38 | 32.06 | -67.32 | 63.95 | 20.5 |\n\n---\n\n## Diagnostic Notes\n\n\n### Why These Keywords Are Overspending\n\nAll 10 keywords share a common pattern: **bids are set above the level that the current conversion rate can sustain at the target ACOS**. The formula `New Bid = Current Bid × (Target ACOS / Actual ACOS)` directly corrects for this by scaling the bid down in proportion to how far ACOS exceeds the target.\n\nKey observations by severity:\n\n| Severity | Keywords | ACOS Range | Bid Cut Range |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 🔴 Critical (>35% ACOS) | `cooling mat for dogs` (phrase), `case trimmer reloading` (phrase), `drop it` (phrase), `dog tooth wipes` (exact) | 33.25%–63.95% | −33% to −68% |\n| 🟡 Moderate (25–35% ACOS) | `cooling mat dogs` (exact), `cooling mat for dog` (exact), `wine glass cover` (exact), `cooling mat dogs` (exact, 2nd instance) | 25.98%–39.89% | −21% to −48% |\n| 🟢 Mild (20.5–25% ACOS) | `cooling pad for dog` (exact), `case trimmer` (phrase) | 23.71%–24.88% | −13% to −18% |\n\n> ⚠️ **Note**: `cooling mat dogs` appears **twice** in the top 10 — once with a $1.77 bid (ACOS 26.75%) and once with a $1.16 bid (ACOS 39.89%). These are likely in **different ad groups or campaigns**. Verify before applying changes to avoid unintended double-adjustment.\n\n---\n\n## Strategy & Implementation Guidance\n\n\n### ⚠️ Critical Context: AI Managed vs. Manually Managed Keywords\n\nBefore applying any manual bid changes, check whether these keywords belong to **AI-managed campaigns** (AI status = enabled). The account has **71 active AI groups**.\n\n- **If the keyword's campaign is AI-managed**: Manual bid overrides will conflict with AI's bid optimization logic. Instead, consider:\n  - Tightening the **Target ACOS** on the relevant AI group to guide AI toward more aggressive cost control\n  - Reducing the **AI Personality** setting (toward 1–2) to make AI more conservative on bids\n  - Ensuring **\"Optimize Base Bids\"** action space is enabled so AI can self-correct\n- **If the keyword is manually managed**: Apply the proposed bids directly as calculated\n\n### Prioritized Action Plan\n\n| Priority | Action | Keywords | Rationale |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Apply bid cuts immediately | `dog tooth wipes` ($1.55→$0.50), `cooling mat for dogs` phrase ($1.37→$0.80), `case trimmer reloading` ($2.40→$1.48) | ACOS >33%; largest absolute spend waste |\n| 2 | Apply bid cuts with monitoring | `drop it` ($0.84→$0.56), `cooling mat dogs` $1.16 instance ($1.16→$0.60) | ACOS >30%; moderate spend |\n| 3 | Apply moderate cuts | Remaining 5 keywords | ACOS 23–27%; lower urgency |\n\n### Projected Spend Impact Summary\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Total current 7d spend (these 10 keywords) | $2,673.80 USD |\n| Total projected 7d spend after adjustments | $1,930.80 USD |\n| Total projected spend reduction | **−$742.99 USD (−27.8%)** |\n\n### Monitoring & Validation\n\n- **Review window**: Re-evaluate performance **7–14 days** after applying changes\n- **Watch for**: Impression/click volume drop (over-correction risk), especially for `dog tooth wipes` where the −67.7% cut is aggressive\n- **Acceptance criteria**: ACOS trending toward 20.50% without significant sales volume loss (>20% drop in conversions would warrant bid recovery)\n- **`cooling pad for dog` and `case trimmer`**: Only mildly above target (−13% to −18% cuts); consider applying these last or in smaller increments to minimize disruption"
