          "content": "# 10 Highest-Spending Keywords Above Account-Target ACOS — New Bid Recommendations\n\n## Data window\n- Window: **2026-04-08 → 2026-05-07 (30 days)**.\n- **Account blended ACOS = 19.34%** (target reference).\n- Account total spend $53,748; total sales $277,949.\n\n## Methodology\nNew bid is scaled by `target_ACOS / current_ACOS`. This is the mechanical \"pull this keyword back to the target\" formula. Projected spend = `clicks × new_bid` (assuming impressions / clicks hold).\n\n## Top 10 keywords currently above target ACOS\n\n| # | Keyword | Match | Campaign (trunc.) | Current ACOS | Current CPC | **New bid** | Proj. spend | Δ spend |\n|---:|---|---|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|\n| 1 | cooling mats for dogs | EXACT | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad NB SP Exact | 24% | $1.90 | **$1.54** | $1,718 | −$395 |\n| 2 | (catch-all auto) | — | Hornady-Fireproof_Safe_for_Guns_and_Valuables SP CAT | 33% | $1.84 | **$1.07** | $958 | −$693 |\n| 3 | cooling mat for dog | EXACT | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad NB SP Exact | 24% | $1.83 | **$1.46** | $1,073 | −$270 |\n| 4 | gun safe | PHRASE | Hornady-RAPiD_Gun_Safes NB SP Phrase | **168%** | $3.74 | **$0.43** | $136 | **−$1,043** |\n| 5 | cooling mat for dogs | PHRASE | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad NB SP Phrase | 23% | $1.71 | **$1.47** | $944 | −$158 |\n| 6 | cooling mat dogs | EXACT | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad NB SP Exact | 28% | $1.93 | **$1.35** | $702 | −$300 |\n| 7 | cooling mat dogs | EXACT | GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad NB SP Exact | 33% | $1.86 | **$1.08** | $488 | −$350 |\n| 8 | loose-match | Auto | Hornady-Rapid_Safe_Night_Guard SP Auto | 42% | $0.85 | **$0.39** | $339 | −$404 |\n| 9 | cooling mat for dogs | EXACT | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad NB SP Exact | 33% | $1.88 | **$1.10** | $338 | −$240 |\n| 10 | drop it | PHRASE | WineRX-Drop_It_Drops BRANDED SP Phrase | 28% | $1.49 | **$1.04** | $384 | −$165 |\n| **Combined** | | | | | | | | **−$4,019** |\n\n## Projected total spend impact\n\nBringing these 10 keywords to account-target ACOS saves approximately **$4,019/mo** (from $12,300 in current spend to $8,280 in projected).\n\nAt the **account's blended ACOS of 19.3%**, the freed $4,019 in budget could generate $20,800 in incremental sales if redeployed to the top 10 winners identified in EV035 / EV057 / EV088.\n\n## Special note: Keyword #4 (`gun safe` PHRASE, 168% ACOS)\n\nThis one alone accounts for **26%** of the total savings ($1,043 out of $4,019). Its CPC of $3.74 is more than double the account's $0.92 avg CPC. The mechanical new bid is $0.43 — but at that bid, the keyword will get almost no impressions. This is really a **\"pause or negate\"** signal more than a \"bid-cut\" signal. Either action achieves the same dollar recovery.\n\n## Which moves are safe vs. risky\n\n- **GPS \"cooling mat\" cluster (#1, #3, #5, #6, #7, #9)** — all near the target (23–33% ACOS). Bid cuts of 15–40% are safe; ACOS pulls toward target without collapsing volume.\n- **Hornady Fireproof_Safe category (#2)** — empty keyword means category targeting. 33% ACOS warrants the bid cut; expect impression drop of ~40%.\n- **Hornady `gun safe` PHRASE (#4)** — see special note above; effectively negate.\n- **Hornady Rapid_Safe_Night_Guard loose-match (#8)** — loose-match is structurally unprofitable on this profile (see EV057); agree with the 54% bid cut, or better, **set to 0 / disable**.\n- **WineRX `drop it` PHRASE (#10)** — 28% ACOS is modestly above target. Gentle bid cut (−30%) will bring it to target without material sales loss.\n\n## What I still don't have\n- **Current keyword bid** in each ad group — the \"new bid\" is computed from observed CPC, but the standing bid could be different from observed CPC (placement modifiers, dynamic bidding). Verify each new bid against actual standing bid.\n- **CVR at the lower bid** — my projection assumes CVR holds, but if the keyword drops from top-of-search to rest-of-search as CPC falls, CVR typically degrades.\n- **Seasonality** — GPS cooling mats are seasonally ramping; cutting bids now may leave money on the table as summer hits. The projected savings may look smaller if sales on these terms are about to surge naturally.\n- **Organic spillover (halo)** — for branded terms (#10 `drop it`), lowering ad bids may reduce halo on branded listings.\n"
