          "content": "# Top-of-Search Placement Modifier Opportunities\n\nQuestion: 5 placement-modifier opportunities — campaigns where adding or adjusting a top-of-search modifier would meaningfully shift performance. Justify each with the placement breakdown.\n\nBusiness data used: Sponsored Products campaign performance, campaign-level top-of-search impression share, placement-level impressions/clicks/spend, and campaign configuration snapshots. Time basis follows the business data, primarily 2026-04-09 to 2026-05-08; row-level date windows vary within that range. Currency is USD as reported in the business data.\n\n## Executive read\n\nThis answer corrects the earlier parsing issue: placement rows do not carry sales or order fields, so placement sales/orders should not be treated as zero. Campaign performance shows $52,851.62 spend, $277,012.66 sales, 5,745 orders, 39,171 clicks, ROAS 5.24, and ACOS 19.1%. I used campaign sales/orders/ROAS to judge quality, then used placement spend/clicks and top-of-search impression share to decide where a TOS modifier is likely to move volume.\n\n## Recommended TOS modifier tests\n\n| priority | campaign | spend | sales | orders | ROAS | ACOS | TOS impression share | placement spend / clicks | action |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | ---: | ---: | ---: | ---: | --- | --- |\n| 1 | GPS-GPetShop_Pet_Pads-MULTI-NB-SB-Exact | $1,005.66 | $8,418.65 | 129 | 8.37 | 11.9% | 1.33% | $1,022.48 / 572 | Add a controlled +10% to +15% TOS test; it has the largest efficient scale among low-TOS campaigns. |\n| 2 | Hornady-Fireproof_Keypad_Safe-B09TQ2CW9L-NB-SP-Auto | $845.94 | $5,857.63 | 33 | 6.92 | 14.4% | 0.22% | $868.83 / 783 | Add +10% TOS; strong ROAS with very low TOS share, but keep the test capped because order count is lower. |\n| 3 | The Green Pet Shop-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad_S-B07XKW55KJ-NB-… | $572.61 | $4,111.13 | 85 | 7.18 | 13.9% | 0.38% | $589.64 / 471 | Add +10% TOS; broad campaign is efficient and barely present at TOS. |\n| 4 | The Green Pet Shop-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad_M-B07XPGKJKM-NB-… | $426.04 | $3,839.29 | 69 | 9.01 | 11.1% | 0.31% | $450.77 / 391 | Add +10% to +15% TOS; strong efficiency and enough sales volume to justify more premium placement. |\n| 5 | GuardianSports-GX_Loop_Headgear-MULTI-NB-SP-PHRASE | $369.32 | $4,171.91 | 57 | 11.30 | 8.9% | 8.93% | $376.68 / 413 | Raise TOS by +10%; efficient non-brand traffic with enough clicks to learn quickly. |\n\n## Why these five\n\n- The five campaigns combine positive conversion evidence with low top-of-search impression share. That is the right pattern for a TOS modifier test: profitable traffic exists, but premium-placement coverage is still thin.\n- I did not recommend increasing TOS for high-spend weak performers such as Hornady-RAPiD_Gun_Safes-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase: it spent $1,550.51 for $1,335.27 sales, ROAS 0.86, ACOS 116.1%.\n- I also did not prioritize GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad-MULTI-NB-SP-Exact despite high sales because it already has heavy spend ($7,747.87) and a more moderate ACOS of 20.9%; if tested, use a smaller +5% step after confirming margin targets.\n\n## Data caveat\n\nThe placement breakdown available here contains impressions, clicks, and spend but not sales/orders by placement type, and the placement type itself is not populated. To calculate true TOS-level ROAS, the missing data needed is placement-level sales/orders or a report that breaks conversions out by top-of-search versus other placements.\n"
