          "content": "> **Assumptions applied:** No time range was specified, so this analysis defaults to the last 30 days (Apr 9 – May 8, 2026). \"Below-average ad spend relative to order volume\" is defined as ASINs whose **Spend/Order ratio falls below the overall portfolio average**. The recommended spend increase represents the additional budget needed to bring each ASIN's Spend/Order ratio up to the portfolio average — serving as a concrete, data-driven baseline. Please let me know if you'd like to adjust any of these parameters.\n\n---\n\n## 🔑 Key Findings\n\n1. **Portfolio average Spend/Order is $9.46.** All 5 identified ASINs are currently spending less per order than this benchmark, meaning they are generating orders at a relatively low ad cost — a signal of under-investment, not inefficiency.\n2. **B006NONHNE is the highest-priority ASIN** — it drives 811 orders (the most of any ASIN in the portfolio) with an excellent ACOS of 10.74%, yet its Spend/Order is only $6.83. Closing this gap alone requires an additional **~$2,131/month**.\n3. **B07R4BSY17 has the largest spend gap** ($4.76/order below average) and a high ACOS of 27.18%, suggesting its under-investment may be contributing to inefficient spend distribution — increasing budget here should be paired with bid/targeting review.\n4. **Total recommended incremental spend across all 5 ASINs: ~$4,577/month** — a targeted reallocation that could meaningfully improve coverage for high-converting products.\n\n---\n\n## 📊 Under-Invested ASINs — Spend Increase Recommendations\n\n\n| ASIN | Current Spend (USD) | Orders | Sales (USD) | ACOS (%) | Spend/Order (USD) | Avg Spend/Order (USD) | Spend Gap vs Avg (USD/Order) | Recommended Spend Increase (USD) |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B006NONHNE\">B006NONHNE</Link> | 5537.63 | 811 | 51563.07 | 10.74 | 6.83 | 9.46 | 2.63 | 2130.79 |\n| <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B07XKW55KJ\">B07XKW55KJ</Link> | 2352.59 | 298 | 15030.28 | 15.65 | 7.89 | 9.46 | 1.56 | 465.15 |\n| <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B07R4BSY17\">B07R4BSY17</Link> | 1118.16 | 238 | 4114.53 | 27.18 | 4.7 | 9.46 | 4.76 | 1132.25 |\n| <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B00C65TXO6\">B00C65TXO6</Link> | 866.43 | 139 | 7869.42 | 11.01 | 6.23 | 9.46 | 3.22 | 447.89 |\n| <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B008Y651RO\">B008Y651RO</Link> | 780.67 | 125 | 3039.79 | 25.68 | 6.25 | 9.46 | 3.21 | 401.27 |\n\n> **Overall portfolio average Spend/Order: $9.46** (based on 219 ASINs with ≥1 order, Apr 9 – May 8, 2026)\n\n---\n\n## 💡 Spend Increase Recommendations by ASIN\n\n\n### 1. <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B006NONHNE\">B006NONHNE</Link> — Increase by **+$2,131/month** ⭐ Highest Priority\n\n- **Current:** $5,538 spend | 811 orders | ACOS 10.74% | $6.83/order\n- **Rationale:** This is your highest-volume ASIN with a best-in-class ACOS of 10.74% — well below the target threshold. Every additional dollar spent here is highly efficient. The $2,131 increase brings it to portfolio-average investment levels, and given its conversion strength, actual returns could exceed the average.\n- **Action:** Increase daily budget on campaigns featuring B006NONHNE. Consider raising bids on top-performing keywords/targets to capture incremental impressions.\n\n---\n\n### 2. <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B07XKW55KJ\">B07XKW55KJ</Link> — Increase by **+$465/month**\n\n- **Current:** $2,353 spend | 298 orders | ACOS 15.65% | $7.89/order\n- **Rationale:** Solid order volume with a healthy ACOS. The spend gap is modest ($1.56/order), making this a low-risk incremental investment.\n- **Action:** Modestly increase campaign budgets or bids for this ASIN. Monitor ACOS closely to ensure it stays within acceptable range as spend scales.\n\n---\n\n### 3. <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B07R4BSY17\">B07R4BSY17</Link> — Increase by **+$1,132/month** ⚠️ Review First\n\n- **Current:** $1,118 spend | 238 orders | ACOS 27.18% | $4.70/order\n- **Rationale:** This ASIN has the largest spend gap ($4.76/order below average) and the highest ACOS among the 5 (27.18%). The under-investment may be intentional due to cost concerns, or it may reflect poor bid/targeting efficiency limiting spend delivery.\n- **Action:** Before increasing budget, audit the targeting and bid structure for this ASIN. If ACOS can be brought down through optimization (negative targeting, bid adjustments), then scale spend toward the $1,132 target. If ACOS remains elevated, consider a partial increase (~$500–600) while monitoring.\n\n---\n\n### 4. <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B00C65TXO6\">B00C65TXO6</Link> — Increase by **+$448/month**\n\n- **Current:** $866 spend | 139 orders | ACOS 11.01% | $6.23/order\n- **Rationale:** Strong ACOS (11.01%) with a meaningful spend gap ($3.22/order). This ASIN is converting efficiently but receiving limited ad support.\n- **Action:** Increase campaign budgets for this ASIN. Given the low ACOS, there is room to be more aggressive with bids to drive additional impressions and orders.\n\n---\n\n### 5. <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B008Y651RO\">B008Y651RO</Link> — Increase by **+$401/month**\n\n- **Current:** $781 spend | 125 orders | ACOS 25.68% | $6.25/order\n- **Rationale:** Similar profile to B07R4BSY17 — moderate order volume but elevated ACOS. The spend gap is $3.21/order.\n- **Action:** Similar to B07R4BSY17, review targeting efficiency before scaling. If ACOS is trending down, proceed with the full $401 increase; otherwise, apply a phased approach.\n\n---\n\n## 📋 Summary: Total Recommended Incremental Spend\n\n| ASIN | Recommended Increase (USD) | Priority |\n|------|---------------------------|----------|\n| <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B006NONHNE\">B006NONHNE</Link> | +$2,131 | 🔴 High — scale immediately |\n| <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B07R4BSY17\">B07R4BSY17</Link> | +$1,132 | 🟡 Medium — optimize first |\n| <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B07XKW55KJ\">B07XKW55KJ</Link> | +$465 | 🟢 Low risk — scale now |\n| <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B00C65TXO6\">B00C65TXO6</Link> | +$448 | 🟢 Low risk — scale now |\n| <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B008Y651RO\">B008Y651RO</Link> | +$401 | 🟡 Medium — optimize first |\n| **Total** | **+$4,577/month** | |\n\n> **Note:** These recommendations are based on closing the gap to the portfolio average Spend/Order ratio. For ASINs with ACOS above 20% (B07R4BSY17, B008Y651RO), it is advisable to first improve targeting efficiency before committing to the full recommended increase."
