          "content": "I have analyzed the provided campaign performance data. \n\nTo maximize your overall return on ad spend (ROAS) and drive more efficient sales, I recommend a **total budget reallocation of $800**. We will pull this budget from three highly inefficient campaigns that are currently bleeding ad spend and redistribute it to three top-performing campaigns that are yielding massive returns but appear to be underfunded.\n\nHere is the strategic reallocation plan:\n\n### 🔻 Phase 1: Budget Reductions (Freeing up $800)\nThese three campaigns are operating at a loss (ROAS < 1.0), meaning you are spending more on clicks than you are generating in sales. \n\n**1. Hornady-RAPiD_Gun_Safes-MULTI-NB-SP-Phrase** (ID: 415009445897554)\n*   **Action:** Reduce budget by **$500**\n*   **Performance Justification:** This is the most inefficient high-spend campaign in the account. It consumed $1,550.51 in ad spend but only generated $1,335.27 in sales, resulting in a dismal ROAS of **0.86**. The CPC is also quite high at $3.13. We need to aggressively scale back spend here to stop the bleeding.\n\n**2. Petkin-Pet_Fingertip_Tooth_Wipes-MULTI-NB-SP-Exact** (ID: 459915732771242)\n*   **Action:** Reduce budget by **$150**\n*   **Performance Justification:** This campaign spent $467.62 to generate just $419.18 in sales (ROAS of **0.89**). With a high CPC of $3.27 and a low CTR of 0.35%, this exact-match campaign is struggling to convert clicks into profitable revenue. \n\n**3. SnapSafe-Treklite_Gun_Safe_Lock_Box-B06XQVYY24-NB-SP-Phrase** (ID: 441522316138822)\n*   **Action:** Reduce budget by **$150**\n*   **Performance Justification:** This campaign has the worst return profile of the group. It spent $309.92 but only brought in $169.16 in sales, yielding a severely unprofitable ROAS of **0.54**. \n\n---\n\n### 🔺 Phase 2: Budget Increases (Reinvesting $800)\nWe will inject the freed $800 into the following three campaigns. These campaigns are demonstrating exceptional efficiency and high ROAS, indicating that additional budget will likely translate directly into profitable sales growth.\n\n**1. Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large-MULTI-Branded-SP-CAT-ASIN** (ID: 96357209146551)\n*   **Action:** Increase budget by **$400**\n*   **Performance Justification:** This campaign is a powerhouse. It generated $2,765.11 in sales from a mere $144.67 in spend, resulting in a phenomenal ROAS of **19.11**. It also boasts a very healthy CTR of 2.46% and a low CPC of $0.49. Given the high purchase volume (123 purchases), this campaign has the capacity to absorb a larger budget increase and scale beautifully.\n\n**2. Guardian Sports-GC_Helmet_Cover_For_Football-Branded-SB-Phrase** (ID: 285597400681656)\n*   **Action:** Increase budget by **$200**\n*   **Performance Justification:** This campaign has the highest ROAS in the dataset at an astonishing **54.16**. It spent only $48.09 to generate $2,604.99 in sales. Furthermore, it has an incredible CTR of 3.83% and a rock-bottom CPC of $0.21. It is severely underfunded and needs immediate budget expansion to capture more impression share.\n\n**3. Hornady-One_Shot-MULTI-Branded-SP-Phrase** (ID: 469175997450882)\n*   **Action:** Increase budget by **$200**\n*   **Performance Justification:** Another highly efficient branded campaign. It drove $2,241.75 in sales on just $65.71 of spend, yielding a massive ROAS of **34.11**. With 87 purchases already recorded on such a small budget, injecting an extra $200 here will help ensure you don't lose out on highly profitable, high-intent branded searches due to budget caps. \n\n### Summary of Impact\nBy shifting **$800** away from non-branded campaigns that are losing money (average ROAS ~0.76) and moving it into highly targeted, branded, and ASIN-targeted campaigns (average ROAS ~35.0), you will immediately improve your account's overall profitability and lower your blended Cost of Sales (ACOS)."
