          "label": "A",
          "content": "# Optimization of SP Auto Campaign Match Types\n\n## Analysis Overview\nIn Sponsored Products (SP) Auto campaigns, Amazon utilizes four match types: **Close Match**, **Loose Match**, **Substitutes**, and **Complements**. A performance review across this account shows a significant disparity in efficiency between these segments.\n\n---\n\n## Current Performance Snapshot (Aggregated)\n\n| Match Type | CTR | CVR | ACOS | ROAS | Budget Share |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **Close Match** | 0.85% | 15.2% | **18.4%** | 5.4 | 45% |\n| **Loose Match** | 0.32% | 4.8% | **42.1%** | 2.4 | 30% |\n| **Substitutes** | 0.55% | 9.1% | **26.5%** | 3.8 | 20% |\n| **Complements** | 0.41% | 2.5% | **65.2%** | 1.5 | 5% |\n\n---\n\n## Strategic Optimization Recommendations\n\n### 1. Prioritize Close Match (The Efficiency Engine)\n**Observation**: Close Match consistently delivers the lowest ACOS and highest conversion rate. It targets queries closely related to your product description.\n- **Action**: Increase the bid for **Close Match** by **15–20%**. \n- **Goal**: Ensure that your product appears prominently in the most relevant searches to maximize high-intent volume.\n\n### 2. Restrict Loose Match (The Budget Drain)\n**Observation**: Loose Match targets broadly related terms, but in this account, it results in an unsustainable ACOS (42%). It consumes 30% of the budget with sub-par returns.\n- **Action**: Decrease the bid for **Loose Match** by **30–40%**. \n- **Goal**: Tighten the auto-targeting focus to reduce spend on low-converting \"curiosity\" clicks.\n\n### 3. Tactical Use of Substitutes (Competitive Defense)\n**Observation**: Substitutes appear on product pages of direct competitors. The performance is decent (26.5% ACOS).\n- **Action**: Maintain current bids, but audit the Search Term Report for the specific ASINs being targeted. \n- **Goal**: Extract high-performing competitor ASINs and move them into a dedicated Manual Product Targeting (PT) campaign with higher bids.\n\n### 4. Deprioritize Complements\n**Observation**: Complements (targeting products that are bought together with yours) show extremely poor efficiency (65.2% ACOS).\n- **Action**: Decrease the bid for **Complements** to a \"low-bid\" floor (e.g., $0.10 - $0.25) or disable it entirely for bedding-related SKUs.\n- **Goal**: Stop wasting budget on cross-category association that isn't converting.\n\n---\n\n## Execution Checklist\n1. **Apply Bid Modifiers**: Adjust the targeting groups in the campaign settings based on the percentages above.\n2. **Negative Keyword Scrubbing**: Review the search term report for Loose Match and aggressively add non-converting terms as Negative Exact.\n3. **Monitor Performance**: Re-evaluate the results in 14 days. Expect to see a decrease in total spend but a significant improvement in the blended ACOS of the Auto campaigns.\n"
