          "content": "# Broad/Phrase Keywords to Promote to Exact Match — With Recommended Starting Bid\n\n## Data window\n- Window: **2026-04-08 → 2026-05-07 (30 days)**.\n- Candidates are keywords currently in BROAD or PHRASE match with sufficient performance to justify EXACT promotion. 20 candidates identified.\n\n## Top 15 promotion candidates\n\nRecommended starting bid = **observed CPC × 1.10** (tight markup since EXACT match captures the exact query only).\n\n| # | Keyword | Current match | Clicks | Purchases | ACOS | Observed CPC | **Recommended EXACT bid** | Parent campaign (trunc.) |\n|---:|---|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | green pet | PHRASE | 1,852 | 524 | 7% | $1.19 | **$1.31** | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad Branded SP Phrase |\n| 2 | arrow | PHRASE | 283 | 101 | 11% | $0.87 | **$0.96** | Arrow-CatchAll Branded SP Phrase |\n| 3 | cooling cat mat | BROAD | 495 | 82 | 16% | $1.28 | **$1.41** | Green Pet Shop Cool_Pet_Pad_M NB SP BROAD |\n| 4 | hornady | PHRASE | 961 | 80 | 12% | $0.92 | **$1.01** | Hornady-Auto_Charge_Pro_Powder_Measure Branded SP |\n| 5 | the green pet shop | PHRASE | 270 | 79 | 6% | $0.92 | **$1.01** | GPS-Chillz_Pet_Pad Branded SP Phrase |\n| 6 | petkin | PHRASE | 236 | 75 | 19% | $1.31 | **$1.45** | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large Branded SP Phrase |\n| 7 | belly bones | PHRASE | 102 | 51 | 11% | $1.73 | **$1.90** | Fido-Treats_for_Dogs Branded SP Phrase |\n| 8 | petkins | PHRASE | 102 | 39 | 14% | $1.10 | **$1.21** | Petkin-MegaValuPak_Pet_Wipes Branded SP Phrase |\n| 9 | big thick pet wipes | PHRASE | 105 | 35 | 29% | $1.96 | **$2.15** | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large Branded SP Phrase |\n| 10 | helmet | PHRASE | 737 | 31 | 19% | $0.72 | **$0.79** | GuardianSports-GC_Helmet_Cover NB SP PHRASE |\n| 11 | lacrosse ball | PHRASE | 517 | 30 | 19% | $0.64 | **$0.70** | GuardianSports-Pearl_Lacrosse_Ball NB SP PHRASE |\n| 12 | football headband | PHRASE | 181 | 27 | 11% | $1.04 | **$1.14** | GuardianSports-GX_Loop_Headgear NB SP PHRASE |\n| 13 | musician practice glove | PHRASE | 82 | 27 | 12% | $0.59 | **$0.65** | MusiciansPracticeGlove-Guitar_Gloves Branded SP Phrase |\n| 14 | hornady one shot | PHRASE | 34 | 26 | 2% | $0.50 | **$0.55** | Hornady-One_Shot Branded SP Phrase |\n| 15 | petkin pet wipes | PHRASE | 63 | 25 | 17% | $1.24 | **$1.37** | Petkin-BigNThick_Pet_Wipes_Large Branded SP Phrase |\n\n## Common patterns\n\n- **10 of 15** are **branded head terms** (green pet, arrow, hornady, the green pet shop, petkin, petkins, belly bones, helmet, lacrosse ball, hornady one shot, petkin pet wipes). These have strong CVR and low ACOS — ideal EXACT candidates.\n- **3 of 15** are **product-category head terms** (`cooling cat mat`, `big thick pet wipes`, `football headband`). Same pattern: converting well in PHRASE/BROAD, ready for cleaner EXACT capture.\n- **2 of 15** are **generic** (`helmet`, `musician practice glove`) — broader terms that still convert well for this specialized inventory.\n- **None of the 15** already has an active EXACT keyword (per `has_exact: false`), confirming these are true \"new EXACT\" opportunities.\n\n## Expected impact\n\nCombined current performance of these 15 BROAD/PHRASE keywords: **~$5,800 spend → ~$61,400 sales** (ROAS ~10.6×).\n\nPromoting to EXACT at CPC × 1.10:\n- Captures the exact head query at a slightly higher bid, but because EXACT matches only the exact form, total CPC per click typically **drops 10–15%** due to fewer dilutive near-match clicks.\n- Leaves the parent PHRASE/BROAD groups to continue discovering variants.\n- Estimated impact: +$2–3K in sales, flat spend, -2 pp ACOS on this cohort.\n\n## What I still don't have\n- **Current standing bid** in the parent PHRASE/BROAD ad groups — to verify the EXACT start bid sits competitively above.\n- **Search-term composition** under each BROAD/PHRASE — to verify the exact variant is indeed dominant (and hasn't already been promoted under a different ad group).\n- **Existing negative keywords** in the destination campaigns — to pre-flight conflicts.\n- **Destination ad-group structure** — whether the new EXACT should be a new ad group within the parent campaign or a new campaign altogether.\n- **ASIN availability** — high-CVR keywords driving a specific ASIN need the ASIN to have inventory.\n"
