          "label": "B",
          "content": "# SB Video Campaign Expansion — Which ASINs Next Based on SP Performance\n\n## Data window\n- Window: **2026-04-08 → 2026-05-07 (30 days)**.\n- SP ASIN report: 867 records, 306 unique SP-advertised ASINs.\n- SB ASIN report: 75 records, 44 unique SB-advertised ASINs.\n- **267 ASINs are advertised on SP but NOT on SB** — the candidate pool for SB Video expansion.\n\n## Selection criteria\nFor SBV expansion, an ASIN should be:\n- Already **proven to convert** on SP (≥ 10 orders, ≥ $500 sales in 30 days).\n- **Not currently running** on SB (so SBV adds incremental reach, not duplicates).\n- Ideally has decent AOV so SBV's higher CPC is supportable.\n\n## Top 15 SBV expansion candidates\n\nOrdered by SP ad-attributed sales (highest-converting products first).\n\n| # | ASIN | SP sales | SP orders | Implied AOV | Priority |\n|---:|---|---:|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | B09TQ2CW9L | $10,813 | 52 | **$208** | Tier-1 — high AOV, high volume |\n| 2 | B081DK7DQH | $6,180 | 31 | $199 | Tier-1 |\n| 3 | B081DJPYM8 | $5,294 | 15 | $353 | Tier-1 — high AOV, moderate volume |\n| 4 | B00DODX6R4 | $4,879 | 60 | $81 | Tier-1 |\n| 5 | B00C65TXO6 | $4,719 | 108 | $44 | Tier-2 (lower AOV) |\n| 6 | B007JT4P88 | $3,959 | 117 | $34 | Tier-2 |\n| 7 | B08SPG6GHF | $3,451 | 56 | $62 | Tier-1 |\n| 8 | B000PD6QJ6 | $3,163 | 28 | $113 | Tier-1 |\n| 9 | B00IRG0BJO | $1,819 | 52 | $35 | Tier-2 |\n| 10 | B007TNXGMK | $1,813 | 75 | $24 | Tier-2 |\n| 11 | B09Z142MJ7 | $1,663 | 16 | $104 | Tier-1 |\n| 12 | B008Y651RO | $1,660 | 66 | $25 | Tier-2 |\n| 13 | B00GRSQC1A | $1,633 | 27 | $60 | Tier-1 |\n| 14 | B076BS6PJK | $1,629 | 56 | $29 | Tier-2 |\n| 15 | B00LXT23RA | $1,499 | 24 | $62 | Tier-1 |\n\n## Recommendations\n\n### Priority 1 — Tier-1 ASINs (high AOV, already converting on SP)\nStart SBV campaigns for these 8 ASINs: **B09TQ2CW9L, B081DK7DQH, B081DJPYM8, B00DODX6R4, B08SPG6GHF, B000PD6QJ6, B09Z142MJ7, B00GRSQC1A, B00LXT23RA**.\n\nEach has:\n- AOV ≥ $60 (SBV CPC of $3–4 is supportable).\n- ≥ $1,500 in SP sales (validated conversion).\n- ≥ 15 orders in 30 days (enough sample to trust).\n\n**Suggested starting structure per ASIN**:\n- 1 SBV campaign, product-collection format with ASIN and 2 sibling ASINs.\n- Custom video 15–30 seconds.\n- Starting daily budget: $30.\n- Target ACOS: 25% (SB video can tolerate higher ACOS because of the halo / NTB benefit).\n- TOS modifier: +20% (SBV at top-of-search is expensive; avoid going much higher on launch).\n\n### Priority 2 — Tier-2 ASINs (lower AOV)\nThe lower-AOV ASINs (B00C65TXO6 $44 AOV, B007JT4P88 $34 AOV, etc.) can work on SBV but require much tighter economics. Wait for Priority 1 to validate SBV's account-level math before launching these.\n\n### What not to do\n- Don't replicate the SBV campaigns already running on the 44 existing SB ASINs. Look at their performance separately and scale/tweak those rather than duplicate.\n- Don't launch SBV for ASINs with < 10 orders/30d — the SP performance isn't proven enough.\n\n## Justification with conversion data\n\n| ASIN | SP 30d sales | SP 30d orders | Why it's SBV-ready |\n|---|---:|---:|---|\n| B09TQ2CW9L | $10,813 | 52 | Highest SP revenue among SB-absent ASINs; validated converter |\n| B081DK7DQH | $6,180 | 31 | AOV ~$200, attractive for SBV at TOS |\n| B081DJPYM8 | $5,294 | 15 | Highest AOV ($353), perfect for SBV where CPC is expensive |\n| B00DODX6R4 | $4,879 | 60 | High order volume — SBV amplifies reach on proven product |\n| B00C65TXO6 | $4,719 | 108 | Highest SP order count (108) — the SP-auto discovery has found a winning keyword set |\n\n## What I still don't have\n- **ACOS per SP ASIN** — spend was not in this data by ASIN. If any of these ASINs are already at 30%+ SP ACOS, SBV (typically higher cost) may make them unprofitable.\n- **Inventory / stock** per ASIN — don't launch SBV for ASINs that are running low.\n- **Listing quality assessment** — SBV needs good main image and A+ content to justify the CPC.\n- **Brand store availability** — SBV campaigns link to a brand store page; need it to exist for that brand.\n- **Competitor SBV density** in each ASIN's category — to estimate starting bid more precisely.\n"
