          "label": "C",
          "content": "Based on the trailing-90-day data provided (February 8, 2026 – May 8, 2026), I have analyzed the campaign performance and month-over-month trends to project your next quarter's Spend, Sales, and ACOS. \n\nHere is your quarterly forecast and the underlying trend analysis.\n\n### 📊 1. Trailing 90-Day Baseline (Feb 8 - May 8)\nTo establish a baseline, I aggregated the performance of the top 100 campaigns provided in your dataset over the exact 90-day period. \n*   **Total Spend:** ~$65,716\n*   **Total Sales:** ~$368,567\n*   **Blended ACOS:** 17.83%\n\n### 📈 2. Observed Trailing Trends\nA month-over-month analysis (`m1` vs. `m2` vs. `m3`) reveals a **massive seasonal shift** that will dictate next quarter's performance:\n*   **Winter Product Drop-off:** Campaigns for \"FrostGuard\" peaked in February (`m1`) but have almost completely tapered off by April/May (`m3`). For example, the *DelkProducts-FrostGuard-Deluxe* campaign dropped from $1,957 in sales in `m1` to just $147 in `m3`.\n*   **Summer Product Explosion:** The account is currently experiencing aggressive, exponential growth in summer-oriented products, specifically the **\"Cool Pet Pad\"**. \n    *   The top campaign (*GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad-MULTI-NB-SP-Exact*) grew from **$398** in sales in February to **$6,114** in March, and exploded to **$39,614** in the April/May period.\n    *   This single product line is accelerating fast enough to more than offset the loss of winter product revenue.\n\n---\n\n### 🔮 3. Next Quarter Forecast (May 9 - Aug 6)\nBecause the upward trajectory of the summer catalog is significantly steeper than the baseline, a flat projection would be inaccurate. Based on the momentum of the cooling pads heading into peak summer, I project a **Trend-Adjusted Growth Scenario**:\n\n| Metric | Trailing 90-Day (Actual) | Next Quarter (Projected) | Q/Q Change |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Spend** | $65,716 | **$82,145** | +25% |\n| **Sales** | $368,567 | **$442,280** | +20% |\n| **ACOS** | 17.83% | **18.57%** | +74 bps |\n\n---\n\n### 📝 Explicit Assumptions\nThis forecast is built on the following explicit assumptions:\n\n1.  **Data Scope:** The baseline is modeled exclusively on the top 100 campaigns provided in the dataset, which represent the primary volume drivers for the account.\n2.  **Net-Positive Seasonality:** We assume the explosive growth of the \"Cool Pet Pad\" and related summer items will continue through the next 90 days (peak summer), driving a 20% net increase in overall account sales despite the complete drop-off of winter products.\n3.  **Spend & Efficiency (ACOS) Degradation:** We project Spend to grow slightly faster (+25%) than Sales (+20%). As summer products enter their peak season, increased market competition will likely drive up Cost-Per-Click (CPC). Therefore, we assume a slight efficiency degradation, pushing the blended ACOS from 17.8% up to roughly 18.6%.\n4.  **Stable Inventory:** The forecast assumes that the hero products (specifically the Cool Pet Pads and Hornady Safes) will remain in stock without inventory interruptions during their peak demand window."
