          "content": "# Quarterly Forecast — Next Quarter's Spend / Sales / ACOS\n\n## Data window\n- Trailing 90 days: **2026-02-08 → 2026-05-08**.\n- Decomposed into three 30-day months (m1, m2, m3, earliest to latest).\n\n## Observed 90-day trend (month over month)\n\n| Month | Window | Spend | Sales | ACOS |\n|---|---|---:|---:|---:|\n| m1 (earliest) | 2026-02-08 → 2026-03-09 | $27,459 | $148,143 | 18.5% |\n| m2 (middle) | 2026-03-09 → 2026-04-08 | $29,782 | $188,742 | 15.8% |\n| m3 (latest) | 2026-04-08 → 2026-05-08 | **$63,426** | **$336,890** | **18.8%** |\n| **90d total** | | $120,667 | $672,516 | 17.9% |\n\n### Key observations from the trend\n- **Month 3 spend more than doubled month 2** ($29,782 → $63,426, +113%). Sales nearly doubled too ($188,742 → $336,890, +79%). ACOS came back up to 18.8%.\n- **Month 1 → Month 2**: modest spend growth (+8%), big sales growth (+27%), ACOS *improved*.\n- **Month 2 → Month 3**: aggressive scale-up, ACOS returned to prior-period level.\n\nThe seasonal pattern is consistent with mid-April cooling-product demand spikes for this multi-brand account (GPS cooling pads, etc.).\n\n## Forecast for next quarter (approximately May-08 → Aug-08)\n\n### Three scenarios with explicit assumptions\n\n#### Conservative (linear extrapolation)\n**Assumption**: month 3's spend level is the new baseline; growth slows to linear 5–8% month over month.\n\n| Metric | Next Q total (projected) |\n|---|---:|\n| Spend | $63K × (1.0 + 1.05 + 1.10) ≈ **$198K** |\n| Sales | $337K × (1.0 + 1.05 + 1.10) ≈ **$1,054K** |\n| ACOS | ~**18.8%** (hold at recent level) |\n\n#### Seasonal (capture summer peak)\n**Assumption**: month 3's acceleration continues into summer — cooling-category products and Prime Day in month 2 of next quarter.\n\n| Metric | Next Q total (projected) |\n|---|---:|\n| Spend | $63K × (1.10 + 1.40 + 1.15) ≈ **$230K** |\n| Sales | $337K × (1.10 + 1.40 + 1.15) ≈ **$1,230K** |\n| ACOS | ~**19.5%** (slight bump from Prime Day + summer auctions) |\n\n#### Aggressive (scale the winners from EV193/EV201 guidance)\n**Assumption**: executing the recommended budget reallocation from EV193, SBV expansion from EV201, and keyword promotions from EV187/EV199.\n\n| Metric | Next Q total (projected) |\n|---|---:|\n| Spend | $63K × (1.15 + 1.30 + 1.25) ≈ **$234K** |\n| Sales | $337K × (1.25 + 1.45 + 1.30) ≈ **$1,348K** |\n| ACOS | ~**17.4%** (efficiency improvements from winner-scaling, waste elimination) |\n\n## Recommended scenario: Seasonal baseline\n\n| Metric | Next quarter projection |\n|---|---:|\n| **Spend** | **~$230K** |\n| **Sales** | **~$1,230K** |\n| **ACOS** | **~19.5%** |\n\n## Explicit assumptions\n\n1. **Account mix holds.** The same brands (GPS, Hornady, Petkin, GuardianSports, etc.) continue to dominate spend shares.\n2. **No major new product launches** or discontinuations. (EV172 showed the top-10 ASIN mix has shifted significantly in the past 90 days — a similar shift could change the forecast.)\n3. **Prime Day 2026 occurs in mid-July** (month 2 of next quarter). Historical pattern = ~2 days of +50% sales lift + +178% spend spike → adds ~$15K to spend, ~$16K to sales.\n4. **Auction CPC inflation** tracks category demand: expect 10–15% CPC increase in summer vs. spring due to seasonal advertiser competition.\n5. **Inventory constraints** on top ASINs (e.g., B07XPGKJKM) are not binding. If they are, lift is capped.\n6. **No macro demand shock** (recession, category disruption, Amazon policy change).\n7. **Xnurta AI-managed campaigns maintain current target-ACOS settings** — changes to targets would shift results substantially.\n\n## Sensitivity\n\n- If Prime Day ACOS hits 34% (as in 2025), pushing full-quarter ACOS up ~1 pp. The other 89 days stay at trend.\n- If a large campaign like `GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad_Medium` doubles again (as it did in month 3), add ~$10K monthly.\n- Inventory stockouts on hero ASINs could cut 5–15% off sales projection.\n\n## What I still don't have\n- **Prior-year same-quarter data** — the cleanest seasonality anchor. Without it, scenarios rely on 90-day trend extrapolation.\n- **Upcoming ASIN launches / discontinuations** — to adjust the product-mix assumption.\n- **Amazon's Prime Day 2026 confirmed dates** — affects monthly distribution of spend.\n- **Planned Xnurta AI target-ACOS changes** — these drive the auto-bidder's behavior and can shift ACOS materially.\n- **Inventory and FBA health** per hero ASIN.\n"
