          "label": "A",
          "content": "> **Note on assumptions:** No time range was specified, so this analysis defaults to the last 7 days (2026-05-02 ~ 2026-05-08). ASINs are ranked by ad spend (descending), and the same ranking is used to compare the sales distribution. If you'd like a different time range or ranking method, just let me know.\n\n---\n\n## Key Findings\n\n1. **Top 5 ASINs are well-balanced** — they absorb 37.5% of spend and generate 37.6% of sales, making them the most proportionate tier in the account.\n2. **Top 6–10 are the most efficient** — they take only 14.6% of spend but deliver 17.3% of sales, suggesting these ASINs are under-invested relative to their earning power.\n3. **Top 11–25 are over-invested** — they consume 22.0% of spend but return only 16.4% of sales, the worst spend-to-sales ratio among all tiers.\n4. **The long tail (246 ASINs) punches above its weight** — accounting for 25.9% of spend but 28.6% of sales, indicating reasonable collective efficiency despite the large number of products.\n\n---\n\n## Tier-Level Summary: Spend vs. Sales Distribution\n\n\n| Tier | # ASINs | Spend (USD) | Spend Share % | Sales (USD) | Sales Share % | Spend/Sales Ratio |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Top 5 | 5 | 4468.43 | 37.54 | 21547.62 | 37.65 | 0.21 |\n| Top 6-10 | 5 | 1740.33 | 14.62 | 9885.1 | 17.27 | 0.18 |\n| Top 11-25 | 15 | 2614.81 | 21.97 | 9405.41 | 16.43 | 0.28 |\n| Rest | 246 | 3080.62 | 25.88 | 16393.88 | 28.64 | 0.19 |\n\n> **Spend/Sales Ratio** = Spend ÷ Sales. A lower ratio means more sales generated per dollar spent (more efficient). A tier is \"over-invested\" when its Spend Share % significantly exceeds its Sales Share %.\n\n---\n\n## Spend vs. Sales Share — Visual Comparison\n\n\n```yaml\nchart:\n  type: \"xychart-beta\"\n  title: \"Spend Share % vs. Sales Share % by Tier\"\n  legend:\n    show: true\n    type: \"selector\"\n  x-axis:\n    data: [\"Top 5\", \"Top 6-10\", \"Top 11-25\", \"Rest\"]\n  y-axis:\n    - name: \"Spend Share %\"\n      type: \"pct\"\n      unit: \"%\"\n    - name: \"Sales Share %\"\n      type: \"pct\"\n      unit: \"%\"\n  series:\n    - type: \"bar\"\n      name: \"Spend Share %\"\n      data: [37.53661525899704, 14.61947431954631, 21.96545922066096, 25.87845120079568]\n    - type: \"bar\"\n      name: \"Sales Share %\"\n      data: [37.6495950430537, 17.271977692204064, 16.433827852630024, 28.64459941211221]\n```\n---\n\n## Top 25 ASIN Detail\n\n\n| Rank | ASIN | Spend (USD) | Spend Share % | Sales (USD) | Sales Share % |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| 1 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B07XDBD4C4\">B07XDBD4C4</Link> | 1386.51 | 11.65 | 3825.11 | 6.68 |\n| 2 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B006NONHNE\">B006NONHNE</Link> | 1206.29 | 10.13 | 10126.93 | 17.69 |\n| 3 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B07XKW55KJ\">B07XKW55KJ</Link> | 708.82 | 5.95 | 3309.68 | 5.78 |\n| 4 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B007JT4P88\">B007JT4P88</Link> | 652.71 | 5.48 | 2706.31 | 4.73 |\n| 5 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B081DK7DQH\">B081DK7DQH</Link> | 514.1 | 4.32 | 1579.59 | 2.76 |\n| 6 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B081DJPYM8\">B081DJPYM8</Link> | 441.22 | 3.71 | 3104.45 | 5.42 |\n| 7 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B000PD6QJ6\">B000PD6QJ6</Link> | 359.9 | 3.02 | 2115.94 | 3.7 |\n| 8 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B08SPG6GHF\">B08SPG6GHF</Link> | 355.87 | 2.99 | 2300.34 | 4.02 |\n| 9 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B006NOO440\">B006NOO440</Link> | 310.07 | 2.6 | 1939.24 | 3.39 |\n| 10 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B01F209RSI\">B01F209RSI</Link> | 273.27 | 2.3 | 425.13 | 0.74 |\n| 11 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B07XPGKJKM\">B07XPGKJKM</Link> | 260.95 | 2.19 | 2279.57 | 3.98 |\n| 12 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B0DNLNQ4T1\">B0DNLNQ4T1</Link> | 249.6 | 2.1 | 624.23 | 1.09 |\n| 13 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B00M45KB58\">B00M45KB58</Link> | 249.51 | 2.1 | 395.09 | 0.69 |\n| 14 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B09TQ2CW9L\">B09TQ2CW9L</Link> | 222.77 | 1.87 | 207.95 | 0.36 |\n| 15 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B00C65TXO6\">B00C65TXO6</Link> | 191.58 | 1.61 | 1554.7 | 2.72 |\n| 16 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B08LHLYHKL\">B08LHLYHKL</Link> | 191.27 | 1.61 | 685.61 | 1.2 |\n| 17 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B003O6MY6U\">B003O6MY6U</Link> | 163.61 | 1.37 | 290.01 | 0.51 |\n| 18 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B0D8JRRSBX\">B0D8JRRSBX</Link> | 148.04 | 1.24 | 296.68 | 0.52 |\n| 19 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B008Y651RO\">B008Y651RO</Link> | 145.29 | 1.22 | 474.26 | 0.83 |\n| 20 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B07YP85FZM\">B07YP85FZM</Link> | 143.88 | 1.21 | 104.97 | 0.18 |\n| 21 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B07C9H3ZX4\">B07C9H3ZX4</Link> | 135.06 | 1.13 | 215.84 | 0.38 |\n| 22 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B07R4BSY17\">B07R4BSY17</Link> | 134.91 | 1.13 | 457.73 | 0.8 |\n| 23 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B09THLGM5Y\">B09THLGM5Y</Link> | 129.53 | 1.09 | 0 | 0 |\n| 24 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B09THKWJVP\">B09THKWJVP</Link> | 127.23 | 1.07 | 378.95 | 0.66 |\n| 25 | <Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B00DODX6R4\">B00DODX6R4</Link> | 121.58 | 1.02 | 1439.82 | 2.52 |\n\n---\n\n## Proportionality Analysis\n\n\n### Is the account spending in proportion to where it's earning?\n\n**Broadly yes at the top, but with notable inefficiencies in the middle tier.**\n\n| Tier | Verdict | Detail |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| **Top 5** | ✅ Proportionate | Spend share (37.5%) ≈ Sales share (37.6%). These are the account's anchor ASINs and are being funded appropriately. |\n| **Top 6–10** | 🟢 Under-invested | Spend share (14.6%) < Sales share (17.3%). These 5 ASINs are generating outsized returns relative to their budget allocation — there may be room to increase investment here. |\n| **Top 11–25** | 🔴 Over-invested | Spend share (22.0%) > Sales share (16.4%). This tier has the highest Spend/Sales ratio (0.278), meaning it costs more per dollar of sales than any other group. Worth reviewing individual ASINs for efficiency. |\n| **Rest (246 ASINs)** | 🟡 Slightly efficient | Spend share (25.9%) < Sales share (28.6%). The long tail collectively earns more than it costs, though individual ASIN performance will vary widely within this group. |\n\n### Notable individual ASINs in the Top 25\n\n- **<Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B006NONHNE\">B006NONHNE</Link>** (Rank 2): Spends 10.1% of total budget but generates **17.7% of total sales** — the single most efficient ASIN in the top tier. Potentially under-budgeted.\n- **<Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B07XDBD4C4\">B07XDBD4C4</Link>** (Rank 1): Highest spend (11.6%) but only 6.7% of sales — the largest spend-to-sales gap in the top 5. Worth monitoring.\n- **<Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B01F209RSI\">B01F209RSI</Link>** (Rank 10): Spends 2.3% but returns only 0.74% of sales — a significant outlier within the Top 6–10 tier that drags down the group's otherwise strong efficiency.\n- **<Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B09THLGM5Y\">B09THLGM5Y</Link>** (Rank 23): $129.53 in spend with **$0 in attributed sales** during this period — a clear candidate for review or pause.\n- **<Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B07YP85FZM\">B07YP85FZM</Link>** (Rank 20) and **<Link entity=\"asin\" name=\"B09TQ2CW9L\">B09TQ2CW9L</Link>** (Rank 14): Both show spend shares well above their sales shares, indicating poor return on ad investment in this window."
