          "label": "C",
          "content": "# ASIN Spend and Sales Concentration Analysis\n\nQuestion: Distribution of ad spend across ASINs: what share goes to the top 5, top 10, top 25, and the rest? Compare to the same distribution of ad-attributed sales. Is the account spending in proportion to where it's earning?\n\nBusiness data used: campaign-level advertising performance, ASIN/product-level attributed sales and orders, campaign configuration, budget, and status snapshots. Time basis: 2026-04-09/2026-05-07; 2026-04-09/2026-05-08; 2026-04-09/2026-05-06. Monetary values follow the numeric currency basis present in the business data; no additional FX conversion was applied.\n\n## Executive read\n\nFrom the available business data, measurable totals are spend $52,851.22, sales $276,599.76, orders 5,739, clicks 39,170, and aggregate ACOS 19.1%. The answer below uses the most relevant dimensions present in the business data; missing fields are called out explicitly.\n\n## Period comparison\n\n| business view / period | rows | spend | sales | orders | ACOS | ROAS |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Business slice 1 | 942 | $0.00 | $276,599.76 | 5,739 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| Business slice 2 | 148 | $52,851.22 | $0.00 | 0 | n/a | 0.00 |\n\n## Key ASIN view\n\n| ASIN | spend | sales | orders | clicks | ACOS | CVR |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| B006NOO440 | $0.00 | $3,144.62 | 36 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B0C5N8G918 | $0.00 | $2,027.49 | 51 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B007OX6PPA | $0.00 | $425.52 | 30 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B08LLDF9Q5 | $0.00 | $274.89 | 11 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B005JEMARS | $0.00 | $619.69 | 28 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B003O6MY6U | $0.00 | $445.40 | 33 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B000BOC4ZY | $0.00 | $151.43 | 12 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B07S9VVVHF | $0.00 | $83.82 | 5 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n\n## Scale candidates\n\nThese have orders and controlled ACOS, so they are the safer places to add incremental traffic:\n\n| ASIN | spend | sales | orders | clicks | ACOS | CVR |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| B006NONHNE | $0.00 | $3,719.38 | 57 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B006NOO440 | $0.00 | $3,144.62 | 36 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B00C65TXO6 | $0.00 | $2,679.33 | 62 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B0C5N8G918 | $0.00 | $2,027.49 | 51 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B0FXY3YSKP | $0.00 | $1,551.90 | 16 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n| B07XKW55KJ | $0.00 | $1,479.63 | 32 | 0 | 0.0% | n/a |\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. Shift spend toward ASINs with stronger order and sales contribution.\n2. Add exact keywords and product targeting for ASINs with proven demand but underdeveloped ad coverage.\n3. For high-spend weak-ASINs, check pricing, reviews, image quality, and query-ASIN fit before scaling.\n4. If the question requires advertised-ASIN spend but the business data only has converted/purchased ASINs, add the advertised-ASIN mapping.\n"
