          "content": "# New ASINs (First Ad Spend in Last 60 Days) — Launch Curve Analysis\n\n## Data window\n- Window: **Last 60 days (approx 2026-03-09 → 2026-05-08)**.\n- New-ASIN criterion: first ad spend within last 60 days.\n- **27 new ASINs identified.**\n\n## Benchmark methodology\nEach new ASIN is compared to the median performance of similar-tenure ASINs at the same days-since-first-spend. Ratio > 1.0 = ahead of benchmark; < 0.8 = behind.\n\n## All 27 new ASINs\n\n| ASIN | Tenure (days) | Spend | Sales | Orders | ACOS | vs. Benchmark | Track |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---|\n| B0G2YJ9KK2 | 58 | $1,993 | $13,000 | 209 | 15% | **260x** | **AHEAD** |\n| B0G2Y8RC8Y | 46 | $1,043 | $6,459 | 124 | 16% | **129x** | **AHEAD** |\n| B0G2YMBV65 | 53 | $682 | $3,903 | 95 | 17% | **78x** | **AHEAD** |\n| B00DODX6R4 | 22 | $588 | $4,879 | 60 | 12% | **122x** | **AHEAD** |\n| B0G2Y6YSML | 40 | $241 | $1,175 | 46 | 21% | **24x** | AHEAD |\n| B09RKHJ5TV | 41 | $127 | $159 | 1 | 80% | 3x | AHEAD (loose) |\n| B084HQ1XFD | 11 | $89 | $1,158 | 2 | 8% | 33x | AHEAD |\n| B0F1Z49NTB | 13 | $73 | $300 | 1 | 24% | 9x | AHEAD |\n| B0F1Z481TL | 6 | $21 | $180 | 1 | 12% | — | — |\n| B08YWQDP4N | 10 | $18 | $22 | 1 | 81% | 0.63 | **BEHIND** |\n| B00TTEEWP2 | 42 | $16 | $90 | — | 17% | 1.8x | AHEAD |\n| B0F1Z88NW6 | 34 | $9 | $115 | — | 8% | 2.6x | AHEAD |\n| B000QRAMNC | 41 | $8 | $60 | — | 14% | 1.2x | AHEAD |\n| B0742KTHL8 | 24 | $7 | $70 | — | 10% | 1.7x | AHEAD |\n| B003O1WOJ2 | 52 | $5 | $45 | — | 10% | 0.90 | BEHIND (borderline) |\n| B0CNTV4RCZ | 43 | $4 | $24 | — | 17% | 0.48 | **BEHIND** |\n| B01H5UO6GG | 26 | $3 | $20 | — | 15% | 0.50 | **BEHIND** |\n| B08SP5GWGF | 15 | $3 | $18 | — | 15% | 0.53 | **BEHIND** |\n| B0FSPQRQNG | 23 | $3 | $40 | — | 7% | 1.0 | ON TRACK |\n| B000GU6ZVC | 55 | $3 | $27 | — | 10% | 0.54 | BEHIND |\n| B072MHJKHH | 25 | $3 | $13 | — | 20% | 0.32 | **BEHIND** |\n| B08SP9P28D | 44 | $2 | $19 | — | 9% | 0.39 | BEHIND |\n| B005KW4ZT0 | 8 | — | — | — | — | — | (too new) |\n| B004SK2ZFQ | 55 | $1 | $9 | — | 10% | 0.17 | **BEHIND** |\n| B008ML0YVE | 20 | $1 | $10 | — | 8% | 0.25 | BEHIND |\n| B015T1WIKO | 40 | $1 | $10 | — | 6% | 0.20 | BEHIND |\n| B015T1WMCS | 40 | $1 | $10 | — | 6% | 0.20 | BEHIND |\n\n## Summary by track\n\n| Track | Count | Combined spend | Combined sales |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|\n| **AHEAD** of benchmark (> 1.0 ratio) | **13** | ~$4,900 | ~$31,800 |\n| ON TRACK (ratio 0.8–1.2) | 1 | $3 | $40 |\n| **BEHIND** (ratio < 0.8) | 11 | ~$45 | ~$250 |\n| Too new to benchmark | 2 | — | — |\n\n## Key observations\n\n### 5 standout launches (ahead of benchmark, substantial scale)\n1. **B0G2YJ9KK2** — $13K sales in 58 days, 15% ACOS, 260× benchmark. Best-in-class launch.\n2. **B0G2Y8RC8Y** — $6.5K sales in 46 days, 16% ACOS, 129×.\n3. **B00DODX6R4** — $4.9K sales in 22 days, 12% ACOS, 122×. Fastest-ramping.\n4. **B0G2YMBV65** — $3.9K sales in 53 days, 17% ACOS, 78×.\n5. **B084HQ1XFD** — $1.2K sales in 11 days, 8% ACOS, 33×. Very early-stage but flying.\n\nThe B0G2Y... cluster (3 ASINs) are the same new product family driving most of the fresh success — consistent with EV172's finding that recent concentration growth is coming from this family.\n\n### Underperformers worth reviewing\n- **B08YWQDP4N** — 10 days, $18 spent, $22 sales, 81% ACOS, 0.63× benchmark. Either pause or restructure.\n- **B0CNTV4RCZ, B01H5UO6GG, B08SP5GWGF, B072MHJKHH, B004SK2ZFQ** — all at 0.20–0.53× benchmark. These are tiny ($1–4 spend) so the dollar impact is negligible, but worth understanding why none of the spend is materializing.\n\n### Long tail of \"barely spent\" new ASINs (11 ASINs with < $10 spend)\nMost have \"BEHIND\" track but with so little spend the signal is noise. Essentially these are auto-targeting by-catch rather than deliberate launches. Ignore until spend scales.\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. **Scale aggressively** on the top 5 ahead-of-benchmark ASINs (B0G2YJ9KK2, B0G2Y8RC8Y, B0G2YMBV65, B00DODX6R4, B084HQ1XFD). Each has ACOS well under target (8–17%). Lift budget 2–3× on these.\n2. **Investigate B08YWQDP4N** — the only meaningful ASIN behind benchmark. Check ASIN price, listing, competitors.\n3. **Ignore the $1–10 spend \"BEHIND\" cohort** — these are auto-match by-catches, not real launches.\n\n## What I still don't have\n- **What benchmark was used** — the ratio `260x` looks suspiciously large; worth confirming the comparison cohort (same category, same tenure bucket).\n- **Listing quality per ASIN** — a new ASIN ahead of benchmark may be benefiting from strong A+ content that won't hold as volume scales.\n- **Inventory** — scaling recommendations depend on stock availability.\n- **Parent-ASIN context** — some of the new ASINs are child variants of existing parents; the parent's halo may explain a lot of the new-ASIN apparent success.\n- **Ad-entity creation date** — the \"first_date\" is the first ad spend date but may not reflect when the ASIN actually launched on Amazon.\n"
