          "label": "C",
          "content": "# Performance Comparison Across Ad Types: SP vs. SB vs. SD\n\n## Analysis Overview\nThis report compares the efficiency (ROAS/ACOS) and volume metrics across the three primary Amazon ad types: **Sponsored Products (SP)**, **Sponsored Brands (SB)**, and **Sponsored Display (SD)** for the current 30-day period.\n\n---\n\n## Cross-Type Performance Matrix\n\n| Ad Type | Spend Share | Sales Share | ROAS | ACOS | CTR | CVR |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **Sponsored Products (SP)** | 91.5% | 91.7% | **5.07** | **19.7%** | 0.45% | 12.8% |\n| **Sponsored Brands (SB)** | 7.2% | 7.4% | **5.22** | **19.2%** | 0.82% | 18.5% |\n| **Sponsored Display (SD)** | 1.3% | 0.9% | **3.55** | **28.2%** | 0.25% | 4.2% |\n\n---\n\n## Key Insights\n\n### 1. SP: The Scalable Engine\n- Sponsored Products command the vast majority of the account's budget (**91.5%**).\n- It maintains a very healthy 5.07 ROAS despite the high volume, proving it is the most reliable driver of both top-line revenue and bottom-line profit.\n\n### 2. SB: The Efficiency Leader\n- Surprisingly, Sponsored Brands is the most efficient ad type in the account, with a **5.22 ROAS** and an incredible **18.5% CVR**.\n- **Opportunity**: SB is currently under-utilized (only 7.2% of spend). Given that its conversion rate is nearly 50% higher than SP, there is a clear mandate to expand SB coverage, particularly into SB Video formats which tend to perform even better.\n\n### 3. SD: The Developing Channel\n- Sponsored Display is currently the weakest performer, with the highest ACOS (28.2%) and lowest ROAS.\n- **Diagnosis**: The low CTR (0.25%) and CVR (4.2%) suggest that the current SD strategy (likely \"Views Remarketing\" or \"Product Targeting\") is not resonating as well as search-based ads. It is currently acting more as a branding play than a direct response tool.\n\n---\n\n## Conclusion and Recommendations\nThe account is heavily reliant on SP, while SB is demonstrating superior efficiency on a smaller scale.\n\n**Strategic Recommendations:**\n1. **Increase SB Exposure**: Aggressively move budget into high-performing SB campaigns until the ROAS equalizes with SP. A target of 12–15% spend share for SB (up from 7%) is recommended.\n2. **Refine SD Strategy**: Audit the SD campaigns. If they are not contributing to incremental growth or brand awareness in a measurable way, consider reallocating half of the SD budget into the higher-performing SB channel.\n3. **SP Maintenance**: Continue the current \"Down-Only\" bidding strategy for SP to maintain the sub-20% ACOS while hunting for new keyword opportunities to sustain volume.\n"
