          "content": "Based on the provided data summaries for the last 30 days (`product_30d.json`) and the prior 30 days (`product_prior30d.json`), I have calculated the Average Order Value (AOV = Total Sales / Total Purchases) for the ASINs that appear in both periods to identify any shifts greater than 20%.\n\nHere is the analysis of the ASINs with overlapping data:\n\n### 🚨 ASINs with >20% AOV Change\n\n**1. ASIN: B0DNKW6V17**\n*   **Prior 30 Days:**\n    *   Total Sales: $239.89\n    *   Total Purchases: 11\n    *   **Prior AOV:** **$21.81** *(Individual orders were consistently priced at $20.99)*\n*   **Last 30 Days:**\n    *   Total Sales: $569.81\n    *   Total Purchases: 19\n    *   **Last 30 AOV:** **$29.99** *(Individual orders were consistently priced at $29.99)*\n*   **AOV Change:** **+37.5%** 📈\n\n**Insight & Recommendation:** \nThe AOV for **B0DNKW6V17** increased by 37.5%. Looking closely at the transaction-level data, the unit price shifted abruptly from $20.99 in the prior 30 days to $29.99 in the last 30 days. This is a clear indicator of a **direct price increase** or the **end of a significant promotion/discount**. \n*   *Actionable Takeaway:* Despite the 37.5% increase in price, the ad-driven purchase volume actually *increased* (from 11 to 19 orders). You should review the conversion rates and ROAS for this ASIN. If conversion rates remained stable despite the price hike, this new price point is highly optimal for profitability.\n\n---\n\n### 📊 Other Overlapping ASINs (For Context)\n\n**2. ASIN: B00D8GT2W0**\n*   **Prior 30 Days:** Total Sales: $17.98 | Purchases: 1 | **AOV: $17.98**\n*   **Last 30 Days:** Total Sales: $17.98 | Purchases: 1 | **AOV: $17.98**\n*   **AOV Change:** **0%** (Stable)\n\n*(Note: All other ASINs in the provided top 100 summaries only registered ad-attributed purchases in one of the two 30-day periods, meaning a period-over-period AOV comparison could not be established for them without pulling extended historical reports).*"
