          "label": "C",
          "content": "Based on the provided performance data, I have isolated the ASINs that generated sales through your campaigns but recorded **$0 in Promoted Sales** (`metric.salesPromoted` = 0). This indicates these products were purchased via brand halo after a shopper clicked an ad for a different product, meaning they are not currently being advertised directly in this dataset.\n\nHere are the Top 10 unadvertised ASINs ranked by Halo Sales, along with a strategic recommendation on whether to advertise them directly.\n\n### Top 10 Unadvertised ASINs by Halo Sales\n\n| Rank | ASIN | Total Halo Sales | Primary Campaigns Driving the Halo Sales |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **1** | **B0G2Y8RC8Y** | **$5,718.85** | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad, Chillz_Pet_Pad |\n| **2** | **B0CN2L4TXB** | **$1,079.96** | GuardianSports-Pearl_Lacrosse_Ball |\n| **3** | **B005JEMARS** | **$879.56** | GPS-GPetShop_Cool_Pet_Pad, Chillz_Pet_Pad |\n| **4** | **B0787CV6KC** | **$103.90** | Hornady-Auto_Charge_Pro / Digital_Pocket_Scale |\n| **5** | **B0D8JR5251** | **$89.91** | GPS-GPetShop_Pet_Pad_Cover |\n| **6** | **B0F1Z88NVZ** | **$79.99** | GuardianSports-Pearl_Lacrosse_Ball |\n| **7** | **B008BSM6R8** | **$51.96** | Petkin-Mega_Pet_Wipes / Paw_Wipes |\n| **8** | **B001F0RCDC** | **$51.96** | Petkin-Paw_Wipes / MegaValuPak |\n| **9** | **B001KN3OIG** | **$50.95** | Hornady-Reloading_Case_Trimmer |\n| **10** | **B01C4QYWDI** | **$47.96** | MusiciansPracticeGlove-Guitar_Gloves |\n\n---\n\n### Strategic Insight: Advertise or Keep Organic?\n\n**1. The \"Heavy Hitters\" (Ranks 1 - 3) 👉 ABSOLUTELY ADVERTISE**\n*   **B0G2Y8RC8Y ($5,718)**, **B0CN2L4TXB ($1,079)**, and **B005JEMARS ($879)** are generating massive revenue purely by riding the coattails of your other advertised products. \n*   **Verdict:** Do not leave these as organic/halo-only. If they are converting this well as a secondary choice, they have proven high relevance and demand. Launch dedicated Sponsored Products campaigns for these ASINs using the exact search terms that are currently driving their halo sales. You are likely leaving impression volume and top-of-search placements on the table by not bidding on them directly.\n\n**2. The \"Mid-Tier Testers\" (Ranks 4 - 6) 👉 TEST IN AD GROUPS**\n*   ASINs like **B0787CV6KC** and **B0D8JR5251** are showing solid proof of concept (~$80-$100 in halo sales). They are clearly relevant cross-sells or variations (e.g., shoppers clicking a Pet Pad ad but buying the Pet Pad Cover).\n*   **Verdict:** Worth adding to your advertised set. Create a \"Test\" or \"Incubator\" ad group for these ASINs with moderate bids. Alternatively, use Sponsored Display cross-selling to target your own advertised ASINs so shoppers see these highly-correlated products immediately on the detail page.\n\n**3. The \"Incidental Halo\" (Ranks 7 - 10) 👉 KEEP ORGANIC (For Now)**\n*   These ASINs are picking up $40-$50 in incidental sales. This is typical variation-swapping behavior (e.g., a shopper clicks an ad for a 3-pack of wipes but buys the single pack).\n*   **Verdict:** Genuinely organic/halo-only for now. Unless these are high-margin priority products, the volume isn't quite high enough to warrant dedicated campaign budgets yet. You can safely let them continue to harvest free halo sales, or toss them into a low-bid \"Catch-All\" Auto campaign to pick up cheap incremental clicks."
